caption:
ここ数年でバリ島ではトリュフチョコを扱うチョコレート専門店が増えましたが、こちらもその一つ！

チャングーにある「Slab Crafted Chocolate（スラブ・クラフテッド・チョコレート）」です☺

Slab Crafted Chocolate（スラブ・クラフテッド・チョコレート） は2023年12月にオープンしたチョコレート専門店で、本格的なチョコレートが楽しめると人気！

チョコレートの種類は、濃厚なトリュフチョコやプラリネだけでなく、ドライマンゴーやドラゴンフルーツにチョコレートをディップしたものや、ココナッツ、アーモンド、ピスタチオを使ったもの、スパイスを使ったものなど種類豊富で、見ているだけでわくわくしてしまいます✨

Slab Crafted Chocolate（スラブ・クラフテッド・チョコレート） のチョコレートはバラで購入が可能で、100g=120,000ルピア（約1,200円）の量り売り！

ギフト用に、好きなチョコレートを選んで箱入りで購入することもできますよ♡

場所はチャングーのバトゥボロン通り。バトゥボロンビーチへ行く道の途中です🚙

少しお高めですが、チョコレート好きさんは訪れてみてはいかがでしょうか🍫

cleaned_caption: Over the past few years, there have been an increase in chocolate specialty shops in Bali that sell truffle chocolate, and this is one of them. Slab Crafted Chocolate in Canggu. Slab Crafted Chocolate is a chocolate specialty shop that opened in December 2023, and is popular for enjoying authentic chocolate. There are many different types of chocolate, including rich truffle chocolate and praline, dried mango and dragon fruit with chocolate dipped, coconut mondo pistachios, and spices, and just looking at it makes me excited. Slab Crafted ChocolateChocolates can be purchased as roses, and sold by weight for around 120,000 rupiah, 100g, 1,200 yen. You can also choose your favorite chocolate as a gift and buy it in a box. The location is on the way to Batuboron Beach in Batuboron Street, Canggu. It's a little expensive, but if you're a chocolate lover, why not visit? caption:
Shoulder dislocations suck. They are super painful, often accompanied by other injuries, and just suck. Unfortunately If you are a surfer and dislocate your shoulder, it might be better to have surgery. 

If you are young and fit, and love to do overhead activities (like surfing ) the chances that you are going to dislocate it again are pretty high (almost inevitable ) . And every time you dislocate it again, you run the risk of damaging other stuff (like the cartilage in your back and socket). So it can pay to get surgery . Bankart repairs are non invasive and they pretty much just go in and stable things back together . 

However if you do choose to treat it conservatively, start light. Small movements and isometrics. These exercises are a combination of mid stage stability exercises. Once your mastered the basic stuff, start progressing to these. Hope this helps ☺️#surfrehab #surftips #surfing #uluwatu #bali #indonesia #padangpadang

caption:
Первый раз на Бали я оказался в 2019 году с компанией друзей, в обычном путешествии на пару недель. 

Даже представить не мог, что спустя годы здесь у меня будет жить столько друзей, знакомых и почти каждое место будет что-то для меня значить и иметь воспоминания. Да и то, что я здесь в сумме проживу больше года.

Не представляю, что испытывают те люди, кто были здесь 10-15 лет назад или еще больше, ведь тут очень все круто меняется. 

Есть конечно в этом и плюсы и минусы. Где-то теряется колорит, больше застройки и людей, но это скорее про конкретные и самые популярные районы. 

Остров большой и в своей глубине он сохраняет свой первозданный вид. 

Мне нравится, то как все меняется и развивается. 

Кто не был на Бали и сомневается из-за множества стереотипов и рилсов – мой вам совет прилететь и проверить все на себе, призма рилсов это не есть вся правда про остров. 

Он правда очень красивый и удивительный, не смотря конечно на свои особенности.
cleaned_caption: The first time in Bali I ended up in 2019 with a company of friends, on a regular trip for a couple of weeks.I could not even imagine that after years I would have so many friends, acquaintances, and almost every place would mean something for me and have memories.And the fact that I have been living here for more than a year.I can’t imagine what those people who were here 1015 years ago or even more are experiencing, because everything is changing very cool here.Of course, there are pros and cons of this.The color is lost somewhere, more buildings and people, but this is more about specific and most popular areas.The island is large and in its depths it retains its original appearance.I like it, how everything changes and develops.Who was not at Bali and doubts due to many stereotypes and realists, my advice to fly and check everything on yourself, the prism of reals is not the whole truth about the island.He is really very beautiful and amazing, despite its own characteristics of course.

caption:
Yeni yaşıma Bali’de girdim!🌎 Hem de yoga ile🧘🏻‍♀️

Yıllardır hep kalabalık partiler vererek kutlardım; mekan, pasta, davet etmek…derken her ne kadar arkadaşlarımla vakit geçirsem de günün sonunda mutlu ama yorgun hissederdim. Belki de işim gereği hem sunuculuklar hem davet hostingleri hep organizasyonların içinde olmak artık doğum günümü farklı kutlama isteğini doğurdu bende🎂🌀

Bu sene Bali’de Ashtanga Yoga üzerine sıkı bir eğitim alıyorum; üstelik dünyanın en iyi hocalarından birinden @kinoyoga 🌎 Eğitim tam bugün 8 Mart’ta doğumgünümde başladı :)

Geçen sene 8 Mart’ta da Hindistan’da @sadhguru liderliğinde derin bir spiritüel invizadayken 1 milyon kişiyle hiç uyumadan meditasyon yaparak Mahashivratri’ye denk gelmiştim🙏🏼

Acaba diyorum her sene kendime böyle bir uzak kaçış yaratsam; gelişim ve dönüşüm yaşasam😇🚀

Yine de seyahate çıkmadan önce evimde yakın arkadaşlarımla kızkıza pasta kesmiştik; dönüşte de yine evde başka bir grupla buluşma olacak🥰

Yaş almak, olgunlaşmak, kendi değerinin iyice farkına varmak ve istediğin hediyeyi vermek… çok güzel…🧡🎁

24 saatten Bali fotoğraflarımla doğumgünü postu koymak istedim🪷

2 hafta daha buradayım; eğitimden fırsat buldukça paylaşırım✍🏼

Uçakta hostesler yaşım için 23 dedi; gülerek 2 katı olduğunu 46’nın bittiğini söyledim; burada da genelde 30 sanılıyor. Makyajsız, temiz cilt, doğal ve örgülü saçlarla daha da küçük gösteriyor olabilirim; metabolik yaşım da 31 ama 1978’de doğan biri olarak bugün 47’e bastım! 😍🧿

caption:
Difficult roads often lead to beautiful destinations 🗻

📍 Lahangan Sweet, Bali, Indonesia 🇮🇩

💭 I had planned to take shots at this location at sunrise. A driver was arranged the previous night for 4AM the following morning, and we made our way up the windy mountain roads in complete darkness except for the car’s headlights. Once we arrived at the unloading spot for vehicles, there were two options: either to hike up for free, or pay 70K IDR for a 4-wheeler to take you up, which we opted for. Once arriving at the top of the mountain, I was expecting a beautiful sunrise but was surprised with heavy fog that limited visibility to a couple of metres 😭😂 A lot of travellers who also went up at the same time decided to leave as soon as they saw that but a couple of us didn’t give up. Winds were 60km/hr+ and I was wearing what’s pictured, so I had to borrow a sleeping bag from the very kind coffee shop owner that was there. To sum it up, this was the view I got after waiting 5 hours, was it worth it? 😉

caption:
Sri Lanka to…
Słyszałem kilka odpowiedzi na ten temat:

a) Takie Małe Indie: 
Tutaj się nie zgodzę - lankijczycy totalnie różnią się od indusòw. Co prawda mam porównanie tylko do północy Indii ale Sri Lanka jest na pewno czystsza i bardziej poukładana. Nie mówię, że pod tym kątem jest idealnie ale to na zdecydowany plus. 

b) Kolejne Bali:
To już jesteś bliże prawdy. Wyspa rozwija się bardzo szybko turystycznie i ma potencjał na podobny rozwój. Kilka razy złapałem się na tym, że widoki są podobne do indonezyjskiej wyspy. Na pewno na plus jest to, że jeszcze nie ma tu tylu turystów. 

Byliście na Sri Lance? Co uważacie?
A może planujecie?

#podróże #podróż #srilanka #sygiriarock #podróżnik #bali
cleaned_caption: Sri Lanka I heard a few answers on this topic and such little India here I will not agree the Lankans totally differ from Indusòw.It is true that I have a comparison only until midnight India but Sri Lanka is certainly cleaner and more arranged.I'm not saying that in this respect it is perfect but it's a definite plus.B The next balls are already closer to the truth.The island develops very quickly and has potential for similar development.Several times I caught that the views are similar to the Indonesian island.For sure, there is not so many tourists here yet.Have you been to Sri Lanka?What do you think?Or maybe you are planning?Travel travel Srilanka Sygiriarock Traveler Bali

caption:
🐬💕 Did you know you can see dolphins in Bali?

We woke up at 5 AM for this sunrise tour, not knowing if we’d even spot any dolphins—especially since the tours had been closed for a week due to strong currents. But we took the chance, paid €20, and hoped for the best…

And guess what? It was SO worth it! We were lucky to see around 30 dolphins swimming right in front of us! 🐬✨

Normally, this tour is even better—you can swim and snorkel with dolphins while watching the sunrise. But the weather wasn’t on our side this time. Still, even as someone who’s scared of waves, I felt safe, and in the end, it was absolutely magical! 🌊💙

A huge thanks to @visit.northbali for this unforgettable experience! If you want the best dolphin tour and to explore the beauty of North Bali, definitely check them out! 🏝️🐬✨

Would you wake up before sunrise for this? Let me know! 👇

I woke up to my alarm at 3am alone in my hostel and hopped in a vintage jeep with 3 other strangers who I ended up cuddling with at the top of the mountain as we waited for the sun to come up over the clouds. 

I don’t think people realize that Indonesia has so much more to offer outside of Bali. 

Booked this tour with Mador Hostel!

caption:
I have a full 30 mobility program for surfers. If you comment the word MOBILITY on this post, I’ll send it to you for FREE ☺️

Ever feel like you can’t get low enough on the surfboard? Feel like you can’t compress adequately to get low for speed generation or getting barrelled ? What that pinching feeling you feel at the front of your hips? Maybe try these exercises 

Inadequate hip mobility may really be affecting your surfing. Not only can it cause pain locally , but it could potentially put more load on the structures down the chain more ( like your knees ) if your hips aren’t nice and mobile , other things might have to work harder to pick up the slack (and then they get injured )

Hip impingement issues, hip flexor pain, and even issues with your glut muscles could all be secondary to poor hip mobility. Hope this helps :) #surfrehab #surfinjury #surfpain #surfing #hippain #canggu #uluwatu #bali #indonesia #trestles #padangpadang

caption:
Patrzę na swoją twarz i śmiejące się oczy w których śmiało iskrzy życie! Tyle rzeczy robię tu pierwszy raz! 🙆‍♀️
Z jakąś taką dziwną aż śmiałością i odwagą 🙏Nie pamiętam kiedy byłam w takim dobrym jasnym miejscu ostatnim razem i wcale nie mam na myśli Bali ☺️✨

Jaką grubą i krętą drogę przeszłam jaką wielkość radość sprawia mi dzielenie się pasją i dobrą energią z innymi🫶🏻
Ile w ostatnich latach się działo, by mogło być tak jak jest 🙆‍♀️

Mam tu wspaniałą grupę kobiet, które spełniają swoje marzenia. Myślę o nich, ale także o wszystkich tych, które piszą do mnie przez te ostatnie dni wiadomości. 

Nie trzeba jechać na drugi koniec świata w poszukiwaniu szczęścia. Wiecie o tym prawda? Najcenniejsza podróż dla mnie to ta do siebie. Która prowadzi do słuchania głosu serca.

Pare dni temu nasz przewodnik pracujący z energia( taki trochę inny Ketut z Jedz módl się i kochaj) powiedział mi że mam energię, która ulecza innych 🙏✨

Nie wiem czy mogłam usłyszeć coś piękniejszego i bardziej wzruszającego… 

Nie wiem czy to prawda, ale jedno wiem na pewno - Bardzo chcę się dzielić tym co dobre! Nie zabiorę Was na Bali! A przynajmniej nie dosłownie, ale możecie się tu przenieść 😉

Najnowszy kurs on line „Into me” czeka na was! 
Wśród kilkudziesięciu praktyk chyba największą część stanowi właśnie ta nagana na Bali. Jest tam sporo pięknej pracy. Takiej dzięki której poczujecie się bliżej SIEBIE, spokojniej! Mam nadzieję że doda Wam odwagi, by o siebie walczyć! Że będzie skrzynią inspiracji! 

Do jutra przedsprzedaż 🫶🏻♥️
Kurs dostępny jest w najniższej cenie i czeka na Ciebie 🧘🏻‍♀️

A jeśli chcecie posłuchać historii o czym jest jak i dlaczego powstał - kilka dni temu nagrałam Wam live’a.

Zakup piękny notes i kolorowe długopisy i zobaczmy co nam się uda razem wyczarować 🫶🏻

Mam wielkie szczęście że mogę znów tu być i tym razem w takiej kobiecej drużynie ♥️

caption: I was finally able to enter the place where I saw my children grow up, the neighborhood where for more than 10 years ( MALIBU ) we lived and created memories, the school of my children, the memories of my marriage the pain of my divorce, my life after my little son recovering, my family and friends my elephant and all my furniture designed by me, the toys and the saddest, the photos, the photos and albums break my soul. Seeing my extremely sad children where they can only remember that the tree house was the only thing that did not burn in the father place. In the storage was my wedding dress that would be the dress that one of my nieces would wear. I’m sorry for all my friends, and neighbors who lost everything. The material returns, but in such a short time, I lost my grandmother, my lawyer in Colombia told me that everything was fine and cheated on me, Creating me impressive losses, two of my friends went with God and saw the sadness in the eyes of one of my friends when losing his sister, my new and strict way of taking care of my health for recent medical results. Anyway... so many things at once. Although no one knows our history, we are all in the constant dance of teaching and learning, that is why before judging, respecting, honoring and embracing. Thanks to my friends who have accompanied me in this long process. Well, only my true friends know the truth, social networks are social and family is family.  Even so I wanted to share with you, even though everything seems good on social media, each person keeps his part of life and fights, so when the great success arrives remember that it did not happen overnight, it happened because the path of life is an accumulation of efforts, work, sacrifice, pain, love, strangled moments and happiness, that no one can see, it is a path that only God and your shadow can know. #ilioveyou #zak #Bali #Baldasar. ❤️‍🩹

caption:
DREAM PLACE ✨🇮🇩🛹🔥
.
This place is @amplitude.skatepark 📍 Not to far from Canggu, Bali 🇮🇩 

So much fun to skate and they also have a street section, indoor small wooden bowl, surf skate area and a small beginner-friendly bowl 👌🏽

The entrance fee is 150k IDR. = around $9 USD 💸
There you can rent a skateboard for 100k IDR = $6 🛹 
Also you can rent helmet and pads ⚠️

The only bad thing is probably that on rainy days, the roof doesn’t provide enough coverage for the skatepark ☔️ 

Let me know if you have any question 🙋🏼‍♂️ 

❤️🔥✨

caption:
The first two months were a dry run. And dry if was 😅 So this month is the start of my new year. So cheers to more freedom for more women in my life. Less decision making and more delegation. Less anxiousness and more serendipity. Less getting ready and more just showing up. Less shame. Way more indifference to other people’s opinions. Less regret and more welcoming new experiences, new people, new ideas and new things.

I need to dream this for myself. I’ll be right back. 🥂

Less regret and more welcoming new experiences, new people, new ideas and new things. I need to dream this for myself. Ill be right back. bali luxetribes baeinbali

caption:
Bali hat die tollsten Restaurants, Cafés und Angebote für Kinder 🫶🏼 das hier haben wir zufällig gefunden, nachdem wir völlig fertig nach einem Kaffee gesucht haben. Aus 5 min wurden 1,5h und wir hatten ein glückliches Kind ♥️ sie hat uns mit eingespannt, war ok, wir dachten wir können etwas entspannt sitzen aber ohne andere Kinder bleibt es dann doch bei uns ☺️

📍Tiny Healthy Family Cafe 0+ 

Die ganze Karte war einfach mal zuckerfrei! Lieb ich, meine Kinder bekommen so gut wie keinen unter 4/5 Jahren (diskutiere nicht, passiert manchmal trotzdem und dann ist es auch ok). Die Portionen gibts für kleine, Erwachsene und Portionen die man sich als Familie teilen kann! Das Spielzeug überwiegend plastikfrei (außer Lego, Stifte und Malzubehör). 

#bali #reisenmitkindern #reiseblogger
cleaned_caption: Bali has the greatest restaurants, cafés and offers for children that we found by chance after we were looking for a coffee.5 minutes became 1.5 hours and we had a happy child. She was involved, was ok, we thought we could sit a bit relaxed, but without other children it stays with us Tiny Healthy Family Cafe 0 The whole card was just sugar -free!I love, my children don't get any less than 45 years of being discussed, sometimes happens anyway and then it's ok.The portions are available for small, adults and portions that you can share as a family!The toy predominantly plastic -free except Lego, pens and painting accessories.Bali Reisen Mit children travel bloggers

caption:
Who says you can't be a mother, be a director, a traveller, influencer; photographer, graphic designer, writer, and wife? Why can't you be all at once?

Often, we set our own limitations in our heads on what we can become. It takes us years to realise that we are all capable. Yes, it is hard work and dedication to get there, but we all can do it. lf you set your mind and your heart to it, you can do anything! The most important thing is to do what you love!
 
To the incredible women who inspire and empower those around you ! Don't ever doubt yourself, and don't give up on your dreams. Take that job, climb that mountain, and do what it takes to make yourself happy. And most importantly, learn to say NO to prioritise you! 

Happy Women's day 💓 

#dream #vacay #TravelIsLife #TravelCaptures #dreamy #hotelsandresorts #bali #fun #adventure #baligasm

caption:
This was one of the top 5 best days of my life. 🦋✨ 🐘💃🏻I still can’t believe it was real and feels surreal to have checked off 3 bucket list items, and all in the same day.🩷

First stop was the Elephant Sanctuary in Bali. 🐘 I’ve always been in awe with elephants, so being able to meet them, wash a cute teenager named Risky, then ride them in the water, and feed them out of our hands was like a dream come true. The connection I felt with these beautiful creatures was indescribable. They are just pure Magic. 🤍

Then we headed to @alasharumbali a place that took my breath away. The views of the rice fields were out of this world, and I got to live my princess fantasy of swinging in a flowing dress, that was pink, obvi 💁🏻‍♀️. Thank you Ricky for being my “Insta boyfriend” for the day. 📸😂

To end the day, we went to the Tirta Empul Temple, where we took part in the traditional purification fountain ritual. 🙏🏻It was a spiritual journey, and each of the 11 fountains represent something different.✨ (More detailed meaning of each fountain in comments). ⛲️

By the time I reached the second fountain, I found myself overwhelmed with emotions. 😭It was like all the struggles, joys, and growth I’ve experienced in my life flooded over me. I felt such an overwhelming sense of gratitude, but also sadness. It was a mix of everything I’ve been through and everything I am learning to heal from. It was a reminder that healing doesn’t happen overnight, but to appreciate just how far I have come.✨🫶🏻💖

Today wasn’t just about ticking things off a list. It was about embracing life’s beauty, healing, and feeling all the feels. Grateful for this human experience and that I get to do it with my best friend @forbesricky ✨🥰

#Grateful #HealingJourney #TirtaEmpul #ElephantSanctuary #BaliVibes #BucketListGoals #BestDayEver #MyLove #LetsTravelTheWorldTogether #Elephants #Bali #Ubud #RiceFields #FlowingDress #PurificationRitual #BreastCancerSurvivor #IfYouCanDreamItYouCanDoIt

caption:
Es hora de reconsiderar lo que es “normal” 😅

Nuestra cultura ha normalizado que salgamos corriendo de casa todos los días de la semana, que cada miembro de la familia siga su propio camino, de lunes a viernes.

Hemos separado la unidad familiar en diferentes lugares, solo para pasar juntos mañanas apuradas y tardes cansadas. 😥

No podemos cambiar la cultura en un día, pero podemos empezar a hacer las cosas diferente. ¡Podemos dejar de aceptarla como algo normal!

¿Qué pasaría si, intencionalmente, en nuestras circunstancias actuales, de la mejor manera posible, nos esforzáramos por aceptar la desaceleración y priorizaramos el pasar tiempo juntos como familias? 🧡 

Para nosotros, el trabajar desde casa siendo nómadas digitales emprendedores y hacer homeschooling, o worldschooling mejor dicho, es una forma en la que elegimos reducir la velocidad y priorizar la conexión familiar 🫶

#viajarconniños #viajarenfamilia #familiaviajera #bali #baliwithkids #niñosviajeros #worldschooling #unschoolers #familyunit #unidadfamiliar #nómadasdigitales #digitalnomadfamily #trabajodesdecasa #reconectando #crianzanatural
cleaned_caption: It is time to reconsider what our culture is normal has normalized that we run home every day of the week, that each family member follows their own way, Monday through Friday.We have separated the family unit in different places, only to spend together morning and tired afternoons.We cannot change the culture in a day, but we can start doing different things.We can stop accepting it as something normal!What would happen if, intentionally, in our current circumstances, in the best possible way, we strive to accept the deceleration and prioritize time to spend time as families?For us, working from home by being digital entrepreneurial nomads and making homeschooling, or worldsholing rather, is a way in which we choose to reduce speed and prioritize the family connection travel traveling with niños travel in Familia Family Viajera Baliwithkids Children ViUsviajeros Worldschooling Unschoolers Family Family Family Family Unit Family Nomad UnitDigitalnomadfamily work in the reconnection of crianating

caption:
🗺️ Itinerario di 15 giorni in INDONESIA🏝️🇮🇩

Il viaggio in Indonesia è stato per noi indimenticabile e questa è un’idea per suddividere le tappe tra Bali, Gili e Komodo!👇🏻

📍1 giorno a Yogyakarta (Java)
- qui abbiamo fatto un tour in giornata con driver che ci ha portati ai templi di Prambanan e Borobudur

📍1 giorno a Nusa Penida 
- abbiamo prenotato tramite @forevervacationbali una speed boat + giro dell’isola con driver (Kelingking beach, Diamond beach, Tree House sono spot imperdibili)

📍7 giorni a Bali 
- 2 a Ubud
- 1 a Munduk
- 1 a Karangasem
- 3 a Sidemen

📍3 giorni alle Isole Gili
- abbiamo alloggiato su Gili T. (la più popolata) e organizzato delle escursioni giornaliere alle altre isole

📍3 giorni a Komodo
- abbiamo fatto una crociera di 3 giorni con @travass.life da Labuan Bajo (barca pulitissima, buon cibo e il team è super disponibile!)

🚗Tra una cittadina e l’altra di Bali ci siamo spostati con i driver, prenotati tramite gli hotel oppure con l’app Grab (solo i più lunghi e con più tappe prenotati in anticipo)

🛵 A Ubud, Sideman e Karangasem abbiamo noleggiato un motorino per visitare tutte le principali tappe della zona, consigliato solo a chi è super capace di guidare nel traffico🤯

⛴️ Per arrivare alle Gili affidatevi solo a compagnie ben recensite, noi con Eka Jaya e Blue Water Express ci siamo trovati benissimo! 
Cercate di fare gli spostamenti la mattina quando il mare è meno mosso. 

📆 Il periodo migliore va da Maggio a Settembre☀️
Noi siamo stati in Agosto che è altissima stagione ed è consigliabile prenotare tutto per tempo!

🤢Non ci sono vaccin1 obbligatori, ma portatevi lo spray per le zanzare e bevete solo acqua in bottiglietta (lavaggio denti compreso)

cleaned_caption: 15 -day itinerary in Indonesia The journey to Indonesia has been unforgettable for us and this is unidel to divide the stages between Bali, Gili and Komodo!1 day at Yogyakarta Java here we made a day tour with drivers that led us to the temples of Prambanan and Borobudur 1 day in Nusa Penida we booked a Speed ​​Boat Dellisola through ForeVervacationbali with Kelingking Beach driver, Diamond Beach, Tree House are unmissable commercials 7 days in Bali 2 a Ubud 1 A MUNDUK 1 AKarangasem 3 in Sidemen 3 days at the Gili islands we stayed on Gili T. The most populated and organized of the daily excursions to the other islands 3 days in Komodo we made a 3 -day cruise with Travass.Life from Labuan Bajo Bair clean, good food and the team is super helpful!Between a town and the Laltra di Bali we moved with the drivers, booked through the hotels or with LAPP Grab only the longest and with more stages booked in advance in Ubud, Sideman and Karangasem we hired a scooter to visit all the main stages of the area, recommended only to those who are super capable of driving in traffic to get to the Gili rely only on well -reviewed companies, we with Eka Jaya and Blue Water and Blue Water.Express we had a great time!Try to move the morning when the sea is less rough.The best time goes from May to September we have been to in August which is very high season and it is advisable to book everything in time!There are no mandatory vaccin1, but bring the spray for mosquitoes and drink only water in bottle washing teeth including Bali Life travel itinerary in Indonesia Travel Blogger Summer Holidays Summer Holidays Indonesia Bali Exploreindonesia Indonesia_Photography Balilife itinerary itinerary Igtravel Traveltips Travel ViRal Onther.Nature NatureLovers TravelPhotography Reelviral Trendingreels Travelbuckerist Traveler Instravel Travelblogger Viralvideos Reelsinstagram Like Placetobe Beautifuldestinations Summer

caption:
Was bedeutet „weit kommen“ im Leben für dich? 

Weißt du, für mich war bis zu einem gewissen Punkt völlig klar, dass nur ein Studium infrage kommt. Mir wurde suggeriert, darauf muss ich hin arbeiten. Als es dann soweit war, wollte ich einfach nicht weiter machen. Ich hatte furchtbare Angst, als „dumm“ dazustehen, war es doch für alle völlig klar, dass das der einzige Weg zum Erfolg ist. Aber was bedeutet Erfolg? Auf jeden Fall nicht das, was andere von dir erwarten. Was Erfolg für dich bedeutet, legst du allein fest. Dein Erfolg darf aussehen wie du es dir tief im Inneren vorstellst. Wenn du einmal alles was du denkst zu wissen beiseite legst und anfängst dir selbst zuzuhören, statt immer nur den anderen. Wenn du das machst, wonach dein Herz schreit, was dein Kopf für gewöhnlich verneint, weil alle anderen Stimmen lauter sind. Lass deine eigene Stimme nicht verstummen. Hör ihr zu ♥️ und dann stellt sich dein ganz eigener Erfolg irgendwann von selbst ein. Nur so kannst du sich die Schritte gehen, die dich zu Glück & Erfolg führen. Nur für dich, deine Familie. Alles andere ist irrelevant, denn niemand lebt dein Leben 🙏🏻 

Mein größter Erfolg ist unser Leben. Das wir so gestalten können wie wir es uns wünschen. Wir reisen, einmal um die Welt und vielleicht noch ein Stückchen weiter, näher zu uns selbst und unserer ganz eigenen Wahrheit & Bestimmung 🙏🏻 

Wann fängst du an, dir zuzuhören 😘

#reisen #reiseblogger #bali
cleaned_caption: What does it mean for you in life?You know, for me it was completely clear to a certain point that only a degree could be considered.I was suggested that I have to work on that.When it was time, I just didn't want to go on.I was a terrible fear of being stupid, since it was completely clear to everyone that this was the only way to success.But what does success mean?In any case, not what others expect from you.You set what success means for you alone.Your success may look as you imagine it to be deep inside.Once you think everything you think aside and start listening to yourself instead of just only the other.If you do that, what your heart is screaming what your head usually denies because all other voices are louder.Don't let your own voice fall silent.Listen to her and then your very own success will be settled by itself at some point.This is the only way to take the steps that will lead you to success.Just for you, your family.Everything else is irrelevant because nobody lives your life my greatest success is our life.That we can design as we want it.We travel, once around the world and maybe a bit further, closer to ourselves and our very own truth Determination When do you start to listen to you travel to travel blogger bali

caption:
Nyobain Rute Bali - Semarang naik Sleeper Bus? Lumayan ide buat mudik juga nih! 🤩

Pertama kali naik sleeper bus itu waktu traveling ke Vietnam tahun 2017, dan jujur belum pernah naik sleeper bus di dalam negeri. Nah pas banget ada acara kemarin, gue sama suami nyobain naik sleeper bus karena ini opsi paling murah buat sampai ke Jawa.

Perjalanannya kurang lebih 15 jam dari Bali ke Semarang. Lumayan lama sih, tapi pas malam lumayan nyenyak pas tidur, cuma sedikit kebangun aja karena di cabin atas (saran pilih cabin bawah aja biar gak terlalu terguncang 😅)

Cuma overall nyaman banget sih naik sleeper bus ini. Snacks nya banyak, trus juga ada pantry dan toilet di belakang jadi gak khawatir nahan pipis selama perjalanan. Kalau kamu mau coba juga gak?!

#sleeperbus #bali #semarang #sleeperbusindonesia #backpackingbarengmardiah
cleaned_caption: Try the Bali Semarang route take the sleeper bus?Not bad for going home too!The first time you took the sleeper bus when I was traveling to Vietnam in 2017, and honestly had never taken a sleeper bus in the country.Well, when there was a event yesterday, I and my husband tried to ride a bus sleeper because this is the cheapest option to get to Java.The journey is approximately 15 hours from Bali to Semarang.It's quite long, but at night it's quite sound when sleeping, just a little wake up because in the cabin on the advice, just choose the cabin below so it's not too shaken just overall really comfortable riding this bus.Snacks a lot, then there is also a pantry and toilet behind so you don't worry about going on pee during the trip.If you want to try it or not?!Sleeperbus Bali Semarang SleeperbusIndonesia BackpackingBarengmardiah

caption:
INI SIH AYUNAN PALING ROMANTIS!!! 😍😍😍

Bayangin main ayunan berduaan sambil mandangin view pantai ditemani hangatnya suasana sunrise! Romantis banget ga sih? 

Nah spot yang satu ini letaknya ada di pantai pemuteran, kalian bisa cari “That Pemuteran Tree” atau “Tanjung Budaya Pemuteran”, nanti kalian bakal ketemu ayunan dan satu satunya pohon bakau disana. Selain itu kakian bisa liat view perbukitan juga di sebelah barat dan timurnya. Ini sih salah satu spot cantik yang wajib kalian kunjungi kalau ke daerah Pemuteran! 

Kalau kesini jangan lupa jaga kebersihan dan jangan buang sampah sembarangan ya! Yuk mampir!

Спасибо @aeroflot за комфортные условия 🔥

Хорошо, что у аэрофлота открылся прямой рейс, чтобы улететь на Бали и добраться домой, но ждём рейсы прямые и в Краснодар для большего удобства как раньше. 

Утро 5 марта началось с вкусного завтрака из любимого отеля, 12.5 часов полёта, несколько часов ожидания в аэропорту проходов всех инстанций, в этот раз приехали за 2,5 часа до вылета и впритирку пришли к посадке, так что приезжайте пораньше в аэропорт Денпасара.

Но благодаря тому, что я организатор своей жизни, успел заранее согласовать время, когда нам нужно встать семьей, время готовности наших завтраков, забора всех чемоданов из номера, времени такси, собрать абсолютно все документы, было договорено беспрепятственное прохождение регистрации заранее и так далее - мы все вовремя успели ✈️

Москва нас встретила небольшим снегом, встречей с родственниками, прохладной морозной погодой и отсутствием зелени, ждём настоящей весны, всех обнимаем, скоро увидимся, ваши Андрей, Лиза @lizzyeffy и Лия💛

caption:
✅ Bali: 4€ = 4 waterfalls 🤝😍🌊

📍Save this place, if you want to see 4 waterfalls in one hike. An epic, yet budget-friendly experience 🤩

Nature lovers, this one’s for you! 🌿💦 Banyu Wana Amertha Waterfall is a meszmerising multi-tiered cascade tucked away in North Bali’s lush jungle. With just a 1.2km scenic walk and a few steps down, you’ll be surrounded by stunning waterfalls and refreshing natural streams 🧚🌿✨

And if you don’t feel like walking: there is a round-trip motorbike ride available for 50K IDR (~€3) to save your energy! 🏍️💨 

💡 Note: please make sure to bring cash 💵 as they only accept cash. Entrance: 40k IDR, parking 2k IDR 🙌

Add this to your Bali itinerary and thank me later! 📍✨

W ostatnim czasie ulubionym u mnie produktem jest ZŁOCISTY PEELING DO CIAŁA Z DROBINKAMI BURSZTYNU AMBER marki @avenacosmetics.

Jest on drobno ziarnisty.

Polecany do pielęgnacji każdego rodzaju skóry w tym suchej, odwodnionej, tłustej, mieszanej, normalnej, a nawet wymagającej regeneracji. Można go stosować 1 do 2 razy w tygodniu.

Zawiera w składzie: glicerynę, zmielony bursztyn, glikol propylenowy, ekstrakt z bursztynu, ekstrakt z kwiatostanu głogu dwuszyjkowego, karbomer, glikol kaprylowy, jak również kwas mlekowy.

Zamknięty w plastikowym zakręcanym opakowaniu o pojemności 300 g.

Ma lekką, średnio gęstą konsystencję przypominającą mus w bursztynowym kolorze. Jego zapach jest subtelny, luksusowy, nieoczywisty, nieco orientalny. Dla mnie rewelacyjny. Poza tym skóra ma ładniejszy, wyrównany koloryt. Nie spowodował u mnie żadnego podrażnienia. Dodatkowo poprawia on mikrokrążenie, pobudza do odbudowy naskórka, dotlenia go. Jestem nim zachwycona. Na pewno sięgnę po kolejne opakowanie. Produkt świetnie spełnia swoją funkcję. Warto się nim zainteresować.

Jaki peeling masz w użyciu? Po jakie najczęściej sięgasz?

caption:
🍃Bigger dreams call for healthier habits and healthier habits require more self discipline🍃
————————————————————————————————
What do you dream of? How much can you risk to go against the norm? What are you willing to risk? 
.
If someone asked you what are your top 5 healthy habits? Could you answer without much thinking? Or would listing your healthy 5 take some time? Does being healthy include both your mind, heart, soul - or just your body?
.
How good are you at self discipline? Or what does your self discipline lack? What’s hard to do? Hard to let go of? Hard to change or take on?
.
How many of these questions can you answer truthfully?
.
Food for thought - at some point(s) in our life the above questions are really worth seriously thinking about. 
.
Dreams = habits + discipline
Bigger dreams = healthier habits + more (self) discipline 
.
In other words, what you do and not do; what and who you say ‘yes’ and ‘no’ to; who and what you surround yourself with; how you shape and water your mindset; and how much you push and climb your own mountains are all a part of your own equation to success and living your dream.
.
Spa time, or rather a few different spa days at Padma Ubud’s wonderful cave spa. Aside from relaxing, deep within myself I searched for answers to a few of these questions.
The view of the jungle outside of my window definitely helped - no lies. 
.
Happy weekend. Don’t just dream - make your dreams a reality. That’s all.
.
.

caption:
Thailand has been the first exotic country I visited on my own. Exotic meaning a country with a culture and natrue totally different from what I had known so far. It awakened my love for the Thai cuisine, stunning temples, paradise beaches, and there is a strong draw, always pulling me back to this beautiful country again. I love the lush and green center or north, the thousands of wats you stumble upon in big and small cities, the sparkling river sunsets or breathtaking ocean views. There are so many reasons to visit Thailand again and again and in this travel guide you find tips on how to explore the best of everything, whether you only have a short time or are planning to spend more time in Southeast Asia.

caption:
Der Maeklong Railway Market (auch Train Market genannt) ist der wohl spektakulärste Markt in ganz Thailand. 

❗️Er ist knapp 75 km von Bangkok entfernt und zählt zu den Top Sehenswürdigkeiten des Landes und garantiert einen unvergesslichen Tagesausflug

Der Maeklong Railway Market existiert bereits seit über 100 Jahren. Einige Jahre nach der Eröffnung entschied man sich dann, eine Güterline nach Bangkok zu bauen, um den Fischfang aus der Küstenregion in die Hauptstadt zu transportieren.

#bangkok #thailand #trainmarket #visitbangkok #visitthailand
cleaned_caption: The Maeklong Railway Market also called Train Market is probably the most spectacular market in all of Thailand.It is almost 75 km from Bangkok and is one of the country's top sights and guarantees an unforgettable day trip by the Maeklong Railway Market for over 100 years.A few years after the opening, they decided to build a freight line to Bangkok to transport the fishing from the coastal region to the capital.Bangkok Thailand Train Market Visitbangkok Visitthailand

There is a great deal of campaign information at the end. Please read at the end. I'm basically a person who eats the dishes I like at any restaurant over and over again, but I don't have any new menus or adventures. I'm really worried about what to eat at this restaurant next. They're all delicious and I have so many favorites that I'm sure I'll always wonder what to order. They were all really delicious!!! The customers were constantly coming in between the restaurants, and there are many regular customers. Daikokuken Fifty Fifth Thong Lor 10002330 Rich seafood tonkotsu tsukemen 260B As it is a restaurant that originated from tsukemen, it's a perfect masterpiece The noodles are well-like in a chunk of delicious flavor.It's understandable that many people say tsukemen when you think of Daikokuken, and it's a new menu!! Vegan Dandan noodles 299B It had a rich, delicious flavor that makes you so rich and delicious that you wouldn't think they used meat, and it was amazing. It's a menu recommended by the restaurant!! Mazesoba 240B It's packed with ingredients and is very satisfying, and the mayonnaise is rich and you'll want to bring it to your mouth. This is the day you want a big punch!!! Limited time only!! Salt beef tongue ramen 299B It's light and easy to eat even for women until the end It's loaded with beef tongue, and it's a great deal, as it's a limited time menu, so hurry up Scallop butter and soy sauce stir-fried with soy sauce 140B I really liked the noodles the next time I came, and the seasoning was perfect and too tasty Homemade juicy gyoza 110B When it comes to ramen, the gyoza is the one I want to eat as a set.It's juicy and goes well with beer, but I don't really understand it, but it probably works ˋˏ Campaign information ˎˊ If you tell me you saw MIA's Instagram, you can get a free gyoza or a beer when you order it and get a bargain. caption:
Tips for visiting Wat Phra Kaew: ⬇️

✅ Dress modestly – No shorts, sleeveless tops, or tight clothing. Cover your shoulders and knees.
✅ Go early – Avoid crowds and the heat by visiting in the morning.
✅ Respect the rules – No photography inside the temple housing the Emerald Buddha.
✅ Stay hydrated – Bangkok’s heat can be intense, so bring water.
✅ Explore nearby – Don’t miss the Grand Palace and Wat Pho

THE best soul food in Thailand 🇹🇭 

I couldn’t count on two hands how many times I’ve been to @qulturepattaya - but it is always a time here, so can you blame me? 😩

👉 They have two restaurants on the same road, one for breakfast and one for dinner. Regardless of which one you go to you will have a good time - BUT, the menu items are different! (This was from the lunch time menu)

MY GO TO’s:
- Creamy salmon Alfredo (dinner menu) 🍣 
- Biscuits with jam (breakfast menu) 🍪
- Grits w/cheese (both menus) 🧀
- Oxtail cheesesteak 🥩 (lunch menu)

caption:
Everything you need to know about the Songkran Festival in Thailand 🇹🇭 

• Dates and Duration: The Songkran Festival typically takes place from April 13th to April 15th each year. However, the celebrations may extend for several days in some areas of Bangkok.

• Water Splashing Tradition: During Songkran, a key tradition is the water splashing ritual, representing purification and washing away of bad luck.

• Cultural and Religious Significance: Beyond the water festivities, Songkran holds deep cultural and religious significance. Many Thais visit temples to make merit, offer prayers, and pour water over Buddha statues as a symbol of cleansing and renewal.

• Traditional Activities: Songkran is also a time for traditional activities such as pouring scented water over the hands of elders as a sign of respect. Everyone participated in cultural parades showcasing Thai costumes and music and enjoying delicious traditional foods.

• Street Parties and Events: Bangkok comes alive during Songkran with vibrant street parties and live music performances. Also, cultural exhibitions and food markets offer a variety of local delicacies. Here, visitors can immerse themselves in the festive spirit while exploring the city’s bustling streets.

• Tips for Visitors: To fully enjoy the Songkran Festival in Bangkok, it’s recommended to wear light clothing. Clothes that can get wet, protect electronic devices with waterproof bags, and participate in the water festivities with respect and good spirits.

• Safety Considerations: While Songkran is a joyful celebration, it’s essential to practice safety precautions. Especially during water-splashing activities on busy streets. Be mindful of traffic, stay hydrated, and follow local guidelines for a safe and enjoyable experience.

caption:
Ok, har knappt hunnit skriva. 
Nu har vi varit 4 dagar i Bangkok. Fem vuxna och tre barn, jetlaggade i en stad som verkligen aldrig sover. Det har gått helt ok att ställa om sömn och alla rutiner men Elias har varit sliten. Även jag 😅

Idag lämnade vi Bangkok för Koh Samet. Vi har bott på Circle Sukhumvit 31, en väldigt fin lägenhet vi hyrt via Airbnb. Ca 6400:- för fyra nätter (5 vuxna 3 barn). Tre stora rum med dubbelsängar, två badrum, kök, vardagsrum och tvättstuga. Kan rekommendera denna lägenhet om man ska bo i Bangkok 1-2 nätter annars skulle jag tagit ett annat boende som har en bättre pool med solstolar för att kunna ha poolhäng en dag iallafall (paus för barnen). Poolen var väldigt fräsch och fin men ligger i skuggan sen var ytan vid poolen väldigt liten och det fanns knappt några stolar att sitta på. 

Vi har köpt egen frukost men ätit lunch och middag ute och njutit av allt gott som finns i detta matparadis.

Vi har:
✔️Varit på vattenpark - vi åkte till Pororo Aqua Park Bangkok som är mindre än Siam Park City
✔️ Druckit många Boba tea (bubble tea) och ätit lunch på Pepper Lunch express som blivit vår bästa restaurangkedja utanför Sverige
✔️Ätit Massaman curry (min favorit), morning glory och Pad Thai 👌🏻🌶️
✔️Shoppat på MBK, ICONSiam, Central World & Siam Paragon 
✔️kollat på Wat Arun, (Wat Pho såg vi förra gången)
✔️Tog taxibåt till Khaosan Road. TIPS! Ta taxibåten från Iconsiam om ni vill se olika sevärdheter. Taxibåten stannar vid de mest populära attraktionerna så man kan hoppa av, gå runt och kolla och sen ta nästa båt vidare med ett dagspass. Det kostar bara 150 bath för en heldag. Trafiken är mycket värre än i Stockholm så att åka taxi tar väldigt lång tid - så ta båten eller tåget om ni kan. För oss var det smidigt att ta en 10-sits Grab (Asiens motsvarighet till Uber) även om det blev lång tid i köer.

.

.
#bangkok #bangkokthailand #thailand #resamedbarn #travelling #travelwithkids
cleaned_caption: Ok, have hardly been able to write.Now we have been 4 days in Bangkok.Five adults and three children, jet laced in a city that really never sleeps.It has been perfectly ok to change sleep and all routines but Elias has been worn.Even today I left Bangkok for Koh Samet.We have lived at Circle Sukhumvit 31, a very nice apartment we rented via Airbnb.About 6400 for four nights 5 adults 3 children.Three large rooms with double beds, two bathrooms, kitchen, living room and laundry room.Can recommend this apartment if you are going to stay in Bangkok 12 nights otherwise I would have taken another accommodation that has a better pool with sun loungers to be able to have a pool hanging one day at least a break for the children.The pool was very fresh and nice but is in the shade then the surface at the pool was very small and there were hardly any chairs to sit on.We have bought our own breakfast but eaten lunch and dinner out and enjoy all good things in this food paradise.We have been to the water park We went to Pororo Aqua Park Bangkok which is less than Siam Park City drank many boba tea Bubble Tea and eaten lunch at Pepper Express which has become our best restaurant chain outside Sweden ate Massama Curry my favorite, Morning Glory and Pad Thai Shoppat at MB, Central Second Sam, Iconsiam, IconsiamWe saw last time took a taxi boat to Khaosan Road.TIP!Take the taxi boat from Iconsiam if you want to see different attractions.The taxi boat stops at the most popular attractions so you can jump off, go around and check and then take the next boat with a day pass.It only costs 150 baths for a full day.Traffic is much worse than in Stockholm so that a taxi takes a very long time so take the boat or train if you can.For us, it was easy to take a 10sit grab Asia's equivalent to Uber, although it was a long time in queues...Bangkok Bangkokkthailand Thailand Travelbarn Travelling TravelwithKids

caption:
✨Travel Far Enough, You Will Meet Yourself✨

🎥✨ Magical Trip to Thailand: Bangkok & Chiang Mai! 🇹🇭

🌕 Loy Krathong Festival – A breathtaking celebration of lights and water! In Chiang Mai, I floated my krathong and watched thousands of lanterns rise into the sky. A moment of gratitude, forgiveness, and a fresh start! 🙏✨

🏙️ Bangkok – Floating markets, street food, and golden temples! From the buzzing Khao San Road to the stunning Grand Palace—plus some great shopping at Platinum Mall! 🌇🍜🛍️

⛰️ Chiang Mai – Temples in the mountains, caring for elephants, and exploring the breathtaking nature of Northern Thailand! 🏕️🐘

Would you love to experience this too? Add Thailand to your bucket list! ✈️💙

caption:
🐳วาฬอัปเดตนิทรรศการของ Mackcha ในอควาเรียม

SEA LIFE | Mackcha: “Sea of Reflection”
@sealifebangkok_official , สยามพารากอน

🐟🐠Sea of Reflection: สมุทร | ภาพ | สะท้อน คือ อีเวนต์พิเศษที่เกิดจากความร่วมมือระหว่าง SEA LIFE Bangkok และ Mackcha (ชรารัตติ์ สาระอาภรณ์) ศิลปินผู้สร้างสรรค์คาแรกเตอร์ “Chalotte” (ชาล็อต) สาวน้อยแห่งท้องทะเล ผู้มีดวงตาและชุดคลุมสีฟ้าเป็นเอกลักษณ์ นิทรรศการครั้งนี้เป็นการนำแนวคิดจากนิทรรศการเดี่ยวครั้งแรกของ Mackcha ในปี 2566 ที่เปรียบเทียบความลึกล้ำของจิตใจของมนุษย์ว่าไม่ต่างจากมหาสมุทร มาต่อยอดสู่นิทรรศการศิลปะเชิงประสบการณ์ที่เปิดโอกาสให้ผู้ชมได้ดำดิ่งสู่ห้วงความคิดและสำรวจตัวตนของตนเอง

ครั้งนี้ น้อง Chalotte จะพาผู้ชมดำดิ่งสู่ก้นบึ้งของมหาสมุทร จุดที่ลึกที่สุด เพื่อให้เราทำความรู้จักกับตัวเองในมุมมองใหม่ ผ่านการออกแบบบรรยากาศ และการจัดแสดงงานศิลปะในอควาเรียม ที่สะท้อนความคิด ความรู้สึก และตัวตนที่อาจถูกมองข้าม

ภายในงาน เต็มไปด้วยไฮไลต์มากมาย ได้แก่

🪸ประติมากรรมใต้น้ำขนาดใหญ่ 2 ชิ้น ที่เป็น Chalotte ในชุดมาสคอตใหม่ที่เธอชื่นชอบ
🦭จุดถ่ายรูปกับเพื่อนสัตว์น้ำของ Chalotte ตามต้นแบบจากภาพวาดของ Mackcha 
🐡ภารกิจตามหาสมบัติแห่งตัวตน พร้อมสะสมตราแสตมป์จากแต่ละจุด เพื่อเก็บเป็นของที่ระลึกสุดพิเศษ
🪼การฉายแอนิเมชันสุดน่ารักของ Chalotte และแมงกะพรุน 
🐚 โซนของที่ระลึกจำนวนจำกัด ที่มีเฉพาะในอีเวนต์นี้เท่านั้น 

เชิญชวนทุกคนนะครับ ผลงานของ Mackcha ไม่เคยทำให้ผิดหวังอยู่แล้ว และครั้งนี้ยิ่งพิเศษขึ้นไปอีกกับการจัดแสดงใน SEA LIFE Bangkok ที่ช่วยเสริมธีมของงานให้โดดเด่นยิ่งขึ้น ใครที่ชอบเที่ยวอควาเรียม หรือเป็นแฟนผลงานของ Mackcha บอกเลยว่า ไม่ควรพลาดครับบบ

📍พิกัด: SEA LIFE Bangkok ชั้นบี 1 สยามพารากอน
🗓️ระยะเวลา: วันนี้ - 30 มิถุนายน 2568
✨ซื้อบัตรเข้าชมทางเว็บไซต์ของ SEA LIFE Bangkok หรือสามารถซื้อหน้างานได้เช่นกัน

caption:
📍อชิพาชิมที่ Sunday Brunch ที่ The Sukhothai Bangkok 🎉✨🥂@thesukhothaibangkok บุฟเฟ่ต์สุดพรีเมี่ยมที่ต้องลอง! 🦞🥩🧀

✨ “ที่สุดของซันเดย์บรันช์ที่สายกินต้องห้ามพลาด!” ✨

เมื่อพูดถึง Sunday Brunch ระดับไอคอนิกของกรุงเทพฯ หนึ่งในที่ที่ต้องมาเยือนให้ได้คือที่ The Sukhothai Bangkok ที่นี่ไม่ได้เป็นแค่บุฟเฟ่ต์ธรรมดา แต่เป็น “มหกรรมอาหารระดับพรีเมี่ยม” ที่รวบรวมวัตถุดิบชั้นเลิศจากทั่วโลก เสิร์ฟแบบจัดเต็มทั้งซีฟู้ดเกรดพรีเมี่ยม เนื้อคุณภาพเยี่ยม อาหารนานาชาติ ขบวนชีสสุดอลังการ และขนมหวานละลานตา และฟังเพลงร้องสดๆจากนักร้องด้วยครับ! 😍

💎 ไฮไลต์เด็ดที่ต้องลอง!
🦞 Seafood on Ice – ล็อบสเตอร์สดหวาน คิงแครบเนื้อแน่น และ หอยนางรม 9 สายพันธุ์ คัดสรรจากแหล่งชั้นนำทั่วโลก เสิร์ฟพร้อมซอสหลากสไตล์ 🍋🦪
🥩 Grilled Station – เนื้อวากิวฉ่ำๆ ละลายในปาก และ ขบวนขาแกะใหญ่โต ย่างสุกกำลังดี หอมกรุ่น เนื้อนุ่ม อร่อยจนต้องขอเบิ้ล! 🍖🔥
🍣 Japanese Corner – ซูชิและซาชิมิสุดพรีเมียม สด หวาน ฉ่ำ คัดมาแต่เกรดท็อป! 🇯🇵🐟
🍕 Italian Delights – พาสต้าโฮมเมด พิซซ่าบางกรอบ และ ขบวนชีสหลากหลายจากทั่วโลก สายชีสต้องร้องว้าว! 🧀🍷
🥘 Indian & Thai Cuisine – แกงอินเดียเข้มข้นหอมเครื่องเทศ อาหารไทยรสชาติจัดจ้าน ครบรส! 🇮🇳🇹🇭
🍰 Dessert Wonderland – มุมขนมหวานที่ต้องร้องว้าว! มาการอง เค้กช็อกโกแลต ครัวซองต์อบใหม่ และของหวานไทยรสละมุน! 🍩🍫

✨ บรรยากาศ & บริการ
หรูหราแต่ไม่อึดอัด อบอุ่นแบบไทยๆ พนักงานบริการระดับ 5 ดาว คอยเติมน้ำ เติมอาหารแบบไม่ขาดมือ นั่งยาวๆ ได้แบบไม่เร่งรีบ สบายสุดๆ! 🌿💛

💰 ราคาเริ่มต้น 3,900++ บาท/ท่าน

caption:
Fancy some Thai food and shop for some Thai snacks at the same place? Ne.nenebubu Thai Mini Mart is the place for it.

I remember years ago, this place started as a Thai mini mart selling all things Thai stuff. Then naturally food came into the picture but with limited seating as it’s mainly a store. But now, they have expanded outside to the roadside curb and the food is buzzing especially at night.

The food is very decent and affordable, and quite yummy. What I like is that they offer something more unusual than the common green curry/tom yam fried rice etc. They have Nut Gaeng Som with Fried Fish (something like sour and spicy fish curry or soup). Radna noodles, something you don’t hear that often at Thai places here, is also available.

And jackfruit sticky rice was nice. Something different to the usual mango sticky rice kan? 

Also they have Kham Lam or Thai burned bamboo sticky rice which is unique here.

Ever had Hoh Muk Pla (steamed custard with fish slice)?

Prices are decent i.e. from below RM10 to RM50 range.

It’s a simple, humble roadside spot so don’t expect IconSiam as it’s located behind some shop lots.  

If you bored with the many commercialized Thai food places out there, this place is a cool bet for something different.

And why it’s called Ne.nenebubu, I’m still confused too. Maybe someone they know is called Nene and she likes Labubu? Oh well.

 📍Ne.Nenebubu,
15, Jalan 2/137B , Resource Industrial Centre , Off OKR , 58200 , KL Off Old Klang Road, 58200, KL.

caption:
A sky train and a local bus later, I arrived in Chinatown, weaving through the crowd, searching for a speakeasy on my list. The air was thick with the scent of fried delights, the streets packed shoulder to shoulder and I quickly concluded that this place is perhaps too crowded for me.

But in the next five days, I found myself in Chinatown three times. There’s something about this labyrinth that pulls you in—lanterns swaying in restless air, a dance of disorder, neon glows, twinkling lights and the endless clank of woks. Everyone selling something. Everyone buying something. Strangers from every corner of the world, huddled on tiny plastic chairs, plates piled high, conversations spilling into the streets, hurried handshakes sealing unseen deals.

The pulse of Chinatown is something else, and I’m glad I could capture its rhythm, colors, and chaos in stunning detail on @vivo_india X200, with its incredible street photography mode, freezing moments in time.

caption:
Did I just climb into a dragon’s mouth for a blessing? Yes. Yes, I did. 🐉✨

The Dragon Temple (Wat Sam Phran) in Bangkok is one of the wildest temples I’ve ever been to—just look at it! A 17-story pink tower wrapped in a gigantic dragon, like something out of a fantasy movie. And at the very top? A quiet, sacred space where we received a blessing from the monks. It felt surreal being up there, away from the city noise, with just the breeze and the sound of chanting.

If you’re in Bangkok and want something beyond the usual temples, this is 100% worth the visit. Just be ready for a little workout—those stairs inside the dragon are no joke! 🏃‍♀️🐉

📍Wat Sam Phran, Bangkok Temple

caption:
🌅❤️As a true sunset lover, I’ve found my paradise at @Sirimahannop in Bangkok! This enchanting restaurant is a replica of the Royal Thai Navy’s last three-masted sailing ship from King Rama V’s reign, adding a touch of history to my dining experience.

Watching the sun sink below the horizon while the city lights reflect on the Chao Phraya River is nothing short of magical. Each evening here feels like a personal celebration of beauty and flavor. With handcrafted cocktails from their secret menu and delectable dishes like house-cured dill salmon, spicy seafood glass noodles, and Genovese noodles, my heart sails with every sunset.

Join me on this unforgettable journey! 🍹✨

It wasn’t until my fourth day in Bangkok did I admit to myself I am going to spend the rest of the week here. I blamed the high-priced domestic flights for this decision making but internally I knew I wasn’t done with Bangkok yet. 

Bangkok is a strange city. It’s one of the most fast paced in the world but if you stay longer you find bouts of stillness and peace in the humdrum of every bustle.
Quickly i realised the best way to travel in Bangkok. You wake up early mornings, sleep through afternoons if need be and adventure around late till the night.

This morning market for example. I had perhaps crossed this lane twice before without a glance, late in the day. But in the mornings at 7, this lane is bustling. With temporary carts and stalls selling fresh fruits and vegetables, hot breakfasts steaming in bowls and plates and locals huddled together to catch up before starting their day. Everything is wrapped up by 10 and it goes back to being the unassuming lane that it is.

Bangkok is full of gems like these. Lanes of Song Wat and Talut Noi, bustling with street paints, coffee shops and art at every corner. What a beautiful contradiction this city is.

All photographs shot on @vivo_india X200

caption:
Bangkok’s best riverside restaurants you CAN’T miss!🌊✨😋🍣🍕🌆

Here are 3 must-visit spots with stunning river views and incredible food! 

1. Dark Waters Rooftop Bar - A peaceful oasis with breathtaking views. It’s quiet, romantic, and the food is unreal! The scallops truffle pasta and prosciutto alfredo were next-level. @darkwaters.10600 

2. Praya Dining  @prayadining – A hidden gem in a historic riverside mansion, only accessible by boat. Feels like dining in an Italian palace! The lamb massaman curry and red curry with lychee and pineapple were so unique—sweet, spicy, and delicious! 

3. Threesixty Rooftop Bar – Insane 360° views of Bangkok and the Chao Phraya River! Perfect for sunset drinks and a relaxed evening with friends. @millenniumhiltonbangkok 

🔥 Pro tip: Book these spots on @hungryhub_th for the best dining deals!

🌿✨ Perdido no paraíso! ✨🌿

Khao Sok, um dos segredos mais bem guardados da Tailândia, é um verdadeiro espetáculo da natureza. Entre montanhas cobertas de selva, um lago de águas esmeralda e cavernas misteriosas, cada canto desse parque nacional parece saído de um sonho.

Aqui, o tempo desacelera… Passeios de caiaque entre falésias imponentes, trilhas em meio à floresta e noites dormindo em bangalôs flutuantes tornam a experiência ainda mais inesquecível. Quem mais colocaria esse destino na lista? 🏕️🌊🐘

caption:
Phra Phuttha Thammawisetthasasada, Wat Prayurawongsawas.

The name “Phra Phuttha Thammawisetthasasada” can be formally translated as:

“The Buddha, the Exalted Teacher of the Supreme Dhamma.”

This conveys the meaning that the Buddha is the supreme teacher who expounds the most excellent Dhamma (teachings of truth and righteousness).

พระนาม “พระพุทธธรรมวิเชษฐศาสดา” สามารถแยกความหมายได้ดังนี้
	•	พระพุทธ หมายถึง พระพุทธเจ้า
	•	ธรรม หมายถึง พระธรรม คำสอนของพระพุทธเจ้า
	•	วิเชษฐ (วิเสษ) หมายถึง ความยอดเยี่ยม ล้ำเลิศ
	•	ศาสดา หมายถึง ครู หรือ ผู้สั่งสอน

เมื่อนำมารวมกัน “พระพุทธธรรมวิเชษฐศาสดา” จึงมีความหมายว่า
“พระพุทธเจ้าผู้เป็นศาสดาอันยอดเยี่ยมแห่งพระธรรม”
หรือ “พระศาสดาผู้ทรงแสดงพระธรรมอันประเสริฐ”

เป็นพระนามที่สื่อถึงความเป็นเลิศของพระพุทธเจ้าในฐานะศาสดาผู้สอนธรรมะอันสูงสุดแก่สรรพสัตว์

caption:
📍 Ultimate Bangkok Travel Guide – Save & Share! 🇹🇭

📅 Best Time to Visit
☀️ November - February (Cool & dry season)

🏨 Budget-Friendly Stays
🏙️ Ibis Styles Bangkok – Affordable & central
🌿 Prince Palace Hotel – Great for families
🏝️ The Yard Hostel – Backpacker-friendly

🍛 Best Indian Restaurants
🍽 Gaggan Anand – Luxury Indian dining 🌟
🍽 Bawarchi Indian Restaurant – Classic flavors
🍽 Charcoal Tandoor Grill – Amazing kebabs

🎟️ Top Activities & Costs
🏯 Grand Palace & Wat Phra Kaew – ₹1,200 ($15)
🛶 Floating Market Tour – ₹800-₹1,600 ($10-$20)
🌆 Rooftop Bar Experience – Price varies 🍸

🛍️ Best Shopping Spots
🛒 Chatuchak Market – Cheap & trendy finds
🛒 Platinum Fashion Mall – Wholesale heaven
🛒 ICONSIAM Mall – Luxury shopping & food court

🚖 Getting Around
🚄 BTS Skytrain – Fast & budget-friendly
🚕 Grab Taxi App – Safer than local taxis
🛺 Tuk-Tuk Rides – Fun but negotiate price!

✈️ Visa & Entry Requirements
🛂 Visa on Arrival (₹4,200/$50 for 15 days)
📌 E-Visa – Apply online before travel

💰 Currency & Payment Tips
💵 Thai Baht (THB) – Carry cash for markets
💳 Cards Accepted – But avoid high ATM fees

🏥 Health & Safety Tips
💊 Travel Insurance – Highly recommended
🚰 Drink Bottled Water – Tap water isn’t safe

🐍 Beware of Scams – Overpriced tuk-tuks, fake gems

🚦 Local Etiquette & Laws
🙏 Respect Temples – No shorts, no shoes inside
🚬 No Smoking in Public – Heavy fines apply
🚗 Traffic Rules – Drive on the left side

🌅 Hidden Gems & Unique Experiences
🌉 Asiatique Riverfront – Night market & river views

🍜 Yaowarat Street Food – Best Chinatown eats
🎭 Calypso Cabaret Show – Must-see entertainment

📍 Want a hassle-free Bangkok trip? Contact us @travel_with_nex for the best packages! 📩✈️

🔹 Disclaimer: Information is subject to change. Please verify details before travel. 🚀

caption:
Some of my favourite places I recommend going to when you’re in Bangkok, locations are below 🫶🏻 

📍Golden Mount Temple (go for sunset!)
📍Wat Sam Phran
📍Erawan Museum
📍Ban Suan Cafè (I have a reel all about this cafe)
📍Wat Pak Nam
📍View Arun rooftop bar, best for golden hour 
📍Ojo bar at the Mahanakon (you can do a pub crawl inside this skyscraper, I have a reel about it on the top of my reels tab. Highly recommend!)

Some spots that that aren’t in the video: Talat Noi area for streetfood, Yarowat Road for shopping, Jacks bar for sundowners, Scarlett’s for happy hour (budget friendly sunset roof bar), Ku Bar for cocktails, Samsen area for streetfood, and my fave park in the city: Lumphini! 

I’ve got every place pinned on Bangkok google maps list, if you’d like me to send it to you then comment ‘BANGKOK’ ❤️ 

And ADD YOUR OWN by commenting below! I’m always looking for new spots to go to! 🥰

caption:
My favourite grab driver in 3 months!

I have not been taking any Thai classes just learning from my friend and making lots of mistakes.

When learning a language a lot of people will hold themself back and be shy to speak but you should allow yourself to make mistakes.

As you can see in this video I made a mistake and he just corrected me and now I have learnt forever because I won’t forget.

Learning from mistakes is very powerful so just practice speaking and have fun.

caption:
Here are the 3 best wholesale markets in Bangkok for 2025:

1. Pratunam Market: Located in the bustling Pratunam area, this market is a shopper’s paradise. It offers a wide variety of products at incredibly reasonable prices. Most of the shops here are wholesale, so you can find great deals on clothes, fashion accessories, and more.

2. December’s: This wholesale market is a must-visit for fashion enthusiasts. It specializes in women’s fashion accessories and clothing, and the prices are very affordable. You can find a wide range of items, from trendy jewelry to stylish dresses. December’s is just a few steps away from Pratunam Market.

3. Platinum Mall: This popular shopping mall is also a great place to find wholesale products. It’s located next to December’s and offers a wide variety of stores, including clothing boutiques, jewelry shops, and electronics stores.

caption:
Tag 28/29 in Thailand.🇹🇭🌞
Liebes Tagebuch✍️💌,
heute waren wir den ganzen Tag in der wunderschönen Stadt Ayutthaya.✨ Wir waren hier zum ersten Mal. Wir sind von Bangkok aus 1h 15mit mit dem Taxi gefahren und haben dann jede Menge an super schönen Tempeln abgeklappert.💫 Mein Tages-Highlight war das Ritual mit den Kerzen im Wasser.🥹 Aber auch die alten Tempel und deren Geschichte fand ich super spannend hehe.🥰 Es ist gerade schon 00:09 Uhr. Morgen möchte ich früh aufstehen und mich an den Pool legen bevor wir dann nachmittags an den Flughafen fahren. Ob Bachir mit an den Pool kommt? Ich glaub er findet das Bett gemütlicher😂🤝 Ich bin soooo dankbar für den Monat in Thailand.🫂🩷 und auch so dankbar, dass ich die Reise mit meiner Community teilen durfte.💭 Hätte mir das mal jemand vor paar Jahren gesagt..🩷So, jetzt ist aber Schluss! Wir essen jetzt noch was kleines und gehen dann schlafen.🫂 Gute Nacht und bis morgen.🩷
Eine Frage geht mir aber nicht aus dem Kopf: ob meine Community Lust hat, auf ein kleines Gewinnspiel? (Siehe letztes Bild) Vielleicht werd ich es gleich in den Kommentaren erfahren.🥰🌙

cleaned_caption: Day 2829 in Thailand.Dear diary, today we were all day in the beautiful city of Ayutthaya.We were here for the first time.We drove a taxi from Bangkok from 1h 15 with a taxi and then have a lot of super beautiful temples.My daylight was the ritual with the candles in the water.But I also found the old temples and their history super exciting.It is already 0009.Tomorrow I would like to get up early and put myself on the pool before we drive to the airport in the afternoon.Will Bachir come to the pool?I think he finds the bed more comfortable I am soooo grateful for the month in Thailand.And so grateful that I was allowed to share the trip with my community.If someone had told me that a few years ago ... but now it's over!We eat something small now and then go to sleep.Good night and until tomorrow.I don't get a question out of my head whether my community wants to go to a little competition?See the last picture maybe I'll find out in the comments right away.Thailand Thailand Reisen Ayutthaya Temple Bangkok traveling

£5 or $6.50 👇 who knew there was Michelin street food?!

Bangkok’s Chinatown Night Market = elite street food heaven. I came hungry, and let me tell you, this was a FEAST for £5.

Here’s what I devoured:
🥟 Chicken gyoza – 93p, crispy, juicy, 10/10
🥤 Fresh pomegranate juice – £1.15, sweet & refreshing
🍜 Pad Thai – 93p, perfectly stir-fried, unreal flavour
🍢 Chicken skewer – 69p, smoky, charred, insanely good
🌽 Grilled corn – 93p, buttery and salty perfection
🥥 Coconut ice cream (vegan & dairy-free) – 58p, SO creamy

The fact that you can eat this well for this cheap is exactly why Bangkok’s night markets are next level. The smells, the sizzling woks, the chaos—it’s all part of the experience. If you’re in Bangkok and not eating your way through Chinatown, you’re doing it wrong.

caption:
Phra Serm, Wat Pathum Wanaram

Phra Serm is a sacred Buddha statue enshrined in the ubosot (ordination hall) of Wat Pathum Wanaram Ratchaworawihan in Bangkok. This Buddha image is one of three statues brought from Vientiane, Laos, during the reign of King Rama III, along with Phra Suk and Phra Sai.

Characteristics of Phra Serm
	•	Depicted in the Maravijaya (Victory over Mara) posture in the Lanchang (Laotian) artistic style
	•	Made of bronze
	•	Approximately 1.65 meters wide and 2 meters tall

History of the Relocation

During the reign of King Rama III, three significant Buddha images were relocated from Vientiane:
	1.	Phra Serm – Now enshrined at Wat Pathum Wanaram, Bangkok
	2.	Phra Suk – Sank into the Mekong River during transport and remains missing to this day
	3.	Phra Sai – Now enshrined at Wat Pho Chai, Nong Khai Province

Significance and Devotion
	•	Phra Serm is highly revered by both Thai and Laotian Buddhists.
	•	It is believed that paying homage to Phra Serm enhances one’s fortune, merit, and success in life.
	•	Devotees often pray for prosperity, career advancement, and good fortune.

Every year during Songkran (Thai New Year), a ceremonial procession is held to bring Phra Serm out for a ritual bathing, allowing devotees to pour water over the statue for blessings.

cleaned_caption: Phra Serm, Wat Pathum Wanaram Phra Serm is a sacred Buddha statue enshrined in the ubosot ordination hall of Wat Pathum Wanaram Ratchaworawihan in Bangkok. This Buddha image is one of three statues brought from Vientiane, Laos, during the reign of King Rama III, along with Phra Suk and Phra Sai. Characteristics of Phra Serm Depicted in the Maravijaya Victory over Mara posture in the Lanchang Laotian artistic style Made of bronze Approximately 1.65 meters wide and 2 meters tall History of the Relocation During the reign of King Rama III, three significant Buddha images were relocated from Vientiane 1. Phra Serm Now enshrined at Wat Pathum Wanaram, Bangkok 2. Phra Suk Sank into the Mekong River during transport and remains missing to this day 3. Phra Sai Now enshrined at Wat Pho Chai, Nong Khai Province Significance and Devotion Phra Serm is highly revered by both Thai and Laotian Buddhists. It is believed that paying homage to Phra Serm enhances ones fortune, merit, and success in life. Devotees often pray for prosperity, career advancement, and good fortune. Every year during Songkran Thai New Year, a ceremonial procession is held to bring Phra Serm out for a ritual bathing, allowing devotees to pour water over the statue for blessings. พระเสรม PhraSerm วดปทมวนาราม WatPathumWanaram พระพทธรปศกดสทธ SacredBuddhaImage เสรมดวง EnhanceFortune บญบารม MeritAndBlessings เวยงจนทน Vientiane ลานชาง LanchangArt พระพทธรปสำคญ ImportantBuddhaStatue สงกรานต SongkranFestival BangkokTemples วดในกรงเทพ ศรทธา FaithAndDevotion bangkok กรงเทพมหานคร siampiya สยามปยะ

caption:
Best thing to do in Bangkok with your friends.

Galaxy Thailand is a fun place where you can bring your friends to have a great time together. It’s located at MBK Center on the 4th floor, zone A. There are 6 rooms in total, each featuring a different game with several modes. The games are quite fun and feel like exercising with friends.

These are the 6 game rooms you experienced:
1. Spiral Galaxy

2: Shuttle Control

3: Eye in the Sky

4: Moon Climbing

5: Space Hoop

6: Eclipse Spotti Like

If you’re at MBK for the day and want to take a break from shopping, stop by and play an hour of games.

Don’t miss this fun experience in Bangkok.

More than just a garden, this is a living chapter of China’s modern history. #SummerPalace #EmpressDowagerCixi #EmperorGuangxu #HundredDaysReform #KunmingLake #ImperialChina #EchoesOfHistory

caption:
Vietnam is a land of breathtaking landscapes, rich history, and vibrant culture. From bustling cities to serene natural wonders, here are some must-visit destinations:

Sapa: Mountain Beauty & Ethnic Culture
	•	Stunning rice terraces & Fansipan Mountain
	•	Traditional villages like Cat Cat

Halong Bay: A Majestic Seascape
	•	Take a day trip from Hanoi or enjoy a 2-day, 1-night cruise through the limestone karsts

Hanoi: The Cultural Heart of Vietnam
	•	Old Quarter
	•	 Hoan Kiem Lake & Ngoc Son Temple
	•	Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum
	•	Experience the unique Train Street
	•	Hoa Lo Prison
	•	Admire the beauty of Tran Quoc Pagoda
	•	Explore the ancient Thang Long Citadel

Ninh Binh: “Halong Bay on Land”
	•	Cruise through the stunning landscapes of Trang An & Tam Coc
	•	Visit the grand Bai Dinh Pagoda

Phong Nha: Vietnam’s Cave Kingdom
	•	Marvel at the wonders of Paradise Cave, Dark Cave, Phong Nha Cave & Son Doong Cave
	•	Have fun at The Duck Stop
	•	Botanical Garden

Hue: Vietnam’s Ancient Imperial City
	•	Step back in time at the Imperial Citadel
	•	Visit the iconic Thien Mu Pagoda
	•	Explore the impressive Khai Dinh Mausoleum
	•	Wander through the eerie Thuy Tien Abandoned Waterpark

Da Nang: Coastal Beauty & Scenic Views
	•	Relax on My Khe Beach
	•	Climb the mystical Marble Mountains
	•	Visit the serene Lady Buddha
	•	Take a cable car ride to Ba Na Hills

Hoi An: The Lantern-Lit Ancient Town
	•	Enchanting Old Town
	•	Cross the historic Japanese Bridge
	•	Cham Islands
	•	Explore the ancient ruins of My Son Sanctuary

Mui Ne: Vietnam’s Desert Oasis
	•	White & Red Sand Dunes
	•	Walk along the magical Fairy Stream
	•	Unwind on Mui Ne’s stunning beaches

Ho Chi Minh City: Vietnam’s Bustling Metropolis
	•	Pink Church
	•	War Remnants Museum
	•	Cu Chi Tunnels
	•  Central Post Office
	•	Stroll along Book Street

Mekong Delta: The Rice Bowl of Vietnam
	•	Experience the vibrant floating markets (Cai Rang & Phong Dien)
	•	Explore charming local villages

caption:
Top Vietnamese dishes to try in Hanoi 👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻

🔹Noodle dishes, especially Pho, is a must in Hanoi. You can probably find this speciality everywhere! Usually pho consist of rice noodles, broth, chicken or beef meat and some herbs. My favourite was the duck pho we had in Don Duck, one of the small restaurants in the Old Quarter specialising on duck dishes. They are even included in the Michelin guide with a Bib Gourmand! You can also try other noodle dishes in Hanoi such as Bun bo nam bo, kind of a noodle salad.
🔹Variations of rice dishes such as Com tam, Ga nuong or Com suon nuong with rice and different buns and dumplings such as Banh goi would be a good choice as well. 
🔹M absolute favourite would be the rolls such as Goi cuon! The filling of herbs, veggies and protein is wrapped in a transparent rice paper and is served with a sauce. You can also try nem ran or cha gio, those are the deep fried rolls with a crispy shell outside.
For the best place with a view over Hoan Kiem Lake, the background for the central legend of Hanoi with the returned sword and the turtle, I’d suggest you go to Cau Go restaurant
🔹 Don’t leave Hanoi without trying ca phe trung, egg coffee that is served everywhere, and it’s absolutely delicious: the best ones were served in Ga Dong Du’ong cafe on the Train street, in the Temple of Literature cafe and by our hotel Le Chanvre.
🔹There are also many super sweet drinks with herbs like lemongrass, fresh coconuts, smoothies and fresh juices too such as Nuoc mia (sugar cane juice). And don’t miss fruit salads Hoa qua dam!
🔹And don’t forget famous Banh mi sandwich

caption:
Vietjet, Vietnam's budget airline, is stirring excitement with an enticing festive promotion, offering international flight tickets starting at just ₹11. This remarkable deal is available for flights from prominent Indian cities like Kochi, Mumbai, Delhi, and Ahmedabad to popular Vietnamese destinations such as Ho Chi Minh City, Da Nang, and Hanoi. The ₹11 fare is part of Vietjet's campaign to promote tourism and attract more visitors to experience the vibrant culture and scenic beauty of Vietnam.

However, there's a catch: this promotional fare is available only on Fridays until December 31, 2025, and excludes peak travel periods and holidays.

Booking Information: Tickets can be purchased online or via the Vietjet Air mobile app. Given the high demand generated by this promotion, it's advisable to book promptly to secure a spot.

Important Terms:

Changes to travel dates or routes will incur additional fees, so travelers should finalize their plans before booking.
If a ticket is canceled, the refund will be issued to the traveler's Vietjet wallet, which can be used for future bookings, rather than being returned to the original payment method.
Expansion of Services: Vietjet is also enhancing its connectivity with India by launching two new direct flights this month from Bengaluru and Hyderabad to Ho Chi Minh City. This expansion will increase the total number of weekly flights between India and Vietnam to 78 across 10 different routes.

caption:
The Golden Magic of Hạ Long Bay, Vietnam

Switching my Instagram from monochrome to color + mono was all about capturing moments like this. Hạ Long Bay is pure magic, especially between 4 PM and 7 PM when the sun dips low, painting the sky and sea in golden hues. Thousands of towering limestone islands, draped in lush rainforests and hidden caves, all glowing under the warmth of the sunset. It’s a place that transports you to a completely different state of mind.

If you have a DSLR and can play a little bit with ISO and Shutter speed, this is your paradise. Cruising between these majestic islands for hours, you’ll capture some of the most breathtaking shots of your life. 

Hạ Long Bay has a way of making you fall even more in love with Vietnam.

caption:
Is Vietnam on your bucket list? If not,
it’s time to ADD this country on your bucketlist 🇻🇳✨

Vietnam: A land full of incredible sights, rich culture, mouthwatering cuisine and unparalleled hospitality.

Here are TOP AREAS that i love during our Vietnam visit:

🌸Hoi An - Hoi An Old Town is a beautifully preserved UNESCO World Heritage Site and is probably one of the most charming towns in Vietnam Its narrow colourful streets, colonial buildings from the 18th century, temple, rich coffee culture and hanging lanterns will make you feel like you just traveled back in time.

🌸Ha Long Bay -The cruise experience in Ha long bay is incredible. From emerald waters to the sunset over those limestone cliff in middle of ocean, it’s an absolutely magical experience.

🌸Hanoi - capital of Vietnam and one of our favorite asian cities! It’s charming place full of restaurants, small shops and amazing culture.

🌸Da Nang- Nestled on central vietnam, Da Nang offers endless tropical vibes with villas nestled in the greens with pristine beachs, local seafood, wondrous wellness. Danang beaches is an experience that shouldn’t be missed.

caption:
Chúc ngon miệng! 🍽️ Dobrú chuť po vietnamsky!🇻🇳🫠

Rada by som vám trošku priblížila vietnamskú gastronómiu očami mamy troch detí – a teda očami niekoho, kto vie, že niekedy je najdôležitejšie, aby deti vôbec niečo zjedli. :)))

Vietnam je skutočná hostina pre chuťové poháriky, no ak máte obavy, že tam nenájdete nič pre svoje deti (či seba), môžem vás uistiť – nájdete úplne všetko! Naše deti – 15, 12 a 4,5 roka – sa samozrejme VEĽMI RADI vrhali na overené jedlá ako fantastické pečené kuracie krídelká, burgre, šunkovo-zeleninové Club sendviče, pizza, či cestoviny Carbonara a Bolognese, ktoré sú dostupné vo väčšine hotelov a reštauráciách. No na druhej strane som šťastná, že starší sa už odvážili skúšať aj vietnamské špeciality – hlavne ikonické PHO (dlho varený vývar s ryžovými rezancami), BUN CHA (grilované mäsko s rezancami), čerstvé jarné rolky či vyprážané BANH XEO plnené krevetami a zeleninou.

A keď už hovoríme o morských plodoch, Vietnam je na ne raj! Na grile sme si vychutnávali tigrie krevety, kalamáre, chobotnice, mušle, kraby, ryby všetkých druhov, a musím povedať – keď vidia deti rodičov, ako s nadšením skúšajú tieto dobroty, pridajú sa aj ony. Nie vždy hneď:), ale chuť objavovať sa buduje postupne❤️🫶🏼

Čo sa týka exotiky, žaby sme na tanieri nemali (hoci sme ich videli na mokrom trhu v Duong Dongu – a to bol zážitok sám o sebe!). To isté platí o hadom mäse a iných špecialitách, ktoré sú pre miestnych bežné, ale pre naše žalúdky už trošku za hranicou komfortu. 😉

A čo ovocie? Ak máte radi sladké chute, Vietnam vás dostane – mango, dračie ovocie, papája, passion fruit, banány, hrozno, ananás… každý deň na stole, vo fresh džúsoch alebo ako perfektná bodka po jedle. Kúpite tiež na každom rohu u predajcov v meste či na plážach🥰

Takže ak sa chystáte do Vietnamu s rodinou – nemusíte sa báť! Či už ste milovníci exotiky alebo si radšej dáte svoju overenú klasiku, vždy si tu nájdete niečo, čo vás zasýti a zároveň poteší.

Keby ste sa ocitli vo Vietname, čo by ste ochutnali ako prvé? Napíšte nám do komentára:) 🍜🐠🥭

cleaned_caption: Having Ngon Miệng!Good taste for Vietnam!I would like to bring you a little closer to the Vietnamese gastronomy through the eyes of the mother of three children and thus the eyes of someone who knows that sometimes it is most important for children to eat anything at all.Vietnam is a real feast for taste buds, but if you are worried that you will not find anything for your children or yourself, I can make sure you will find everything!Our children 15, 12 and 4.5 years of course were very happy to throw on proven dishes such as fantastic roast chicken wings, burgers, ham -green club sandwiches, pizza, or Carbonara and Bolognese, which are available in most hotels and restaurants.But on the other hand, I am happy that the elders have already dared to try Vietnamese specialties, especially the iconic Pho, a long cooked broth with rice noodles, Bun grilled meat with noodles, fresh spring rolls or fried banh xeo filled with shrimp and vegetables.And when we talk about seafood, Vietnam is paradise for them!On the grill we enjoyed the tiger shrimp, kalamatics, octopus, shells, crabs, fish of all kinds, and I have to say when they see children's children, they are enthusiastic about trying these goodies, they will also join them.Not always immediately, but the desire to appear is being built gradually in terms of exoticism, we did not have a frog on the plate even though we saw them on the wet market in the Donga and it was an experience in itself!.The same applies to the snake of meat and other specialties that are common for the locals, but for our stomachs a little beyond the limit of comfort.What about the fruit?If you like sweet tastes, Vietnam will get you mango, dragon fruit, papaya, passion fruit, bananas, grapes, pineapple every day on the table, in the fresh juice or as a perfect dot after a meal.You can also buy at every corner with dealers in the city or on the beaches so if you are going to Vietnam with your family you don't have to worry!Whether you are exotic lovers or prefer to have your proven classic, you will always find something that will feed you and please.If you were in Vietnam, what would you taste first?Write caption:
A few morning shots from Hanoi. For me, morning is the best time for shooting because it makes even a bustling city like Hanoi feel calmer and more peaceful.

Plus, mornings often have a magical light—soft and pleasant, making it easy to shoot and edit. It helps create an enchanting atmosphere in the shots. I always recommend exploring new cities early in the morning, especially in touristy areas—you’ll see the city in a way you never have before.

All the photos are edited with my new Echo Preset Pack, which I’ve been using for all my shots over the past year. You can get it too via the link in my bio if you want to edit like me or just learn how to achieve these colors.

caption:
Yuzu Omakase Hanoi
Nhà hàng Omakase nổi tiếng của Thái Lan, đã có mặt tại Sài Gòn và gần đây đã cập bến Thủ đô.
Cả bữa ăn hơn 20 món như một chuyến hành trình khám phá, với những màn trình diễn tương tác món ăn đáng nhớ như sashimi bồng bềnh trong quả cầu pha lê khói, bữa tiệc lấp lánh phủ vàng, hay tráng miệng hái trái yuzu độc đáo. Sự fusion mới mẻ trong món ăn mà vẫn có thể cảm nhận được nguyên liệu cao cấp, tươi ngon theo mùa như cá Kinmedai, cá khờ, sò huyết, ti.nh hoàn cá tuyết, nhung biển, trứng cá tầm Caviar, nấm Truffle quý hiếm của miền Bắc nước Ý, gan ngỗng Pháp, bò Wagyu A5,…
Với không gian sang trọng đậm chất nghệ thuật lấy cảm hứng từ làng gốm Bát Tràng, cùng các phòng private rất thích hợp cho những cuộc hẹn nha
——-
Yuzu Omakase - 17 Thái Phiên, Hà Nội
(6tr5++/pax)

#Omakase #YuzuOmakase #Hanoi
