caption:
Cloudy Hanoi ☁️ Gelandet sind wir bei 25 Grad und schönem Wetter. Mittlerweile sind wir in HaLong angekommen, um morgen unsere HaLong Bay Cruise zu machen und es sind einfach nur noch 14 Grad - wirklich kalt und das bei dickem Wolkenhimmel. 🤯 Eigentlich wollten wir danach nach Ninh Binh in die Reisfelder, aber bei dann 12-14 Grad, Wolken & Regen macht uns das keinen Spaß. 🙈 Daher planen wir jetzt um. 👀 Ab in den Süden und mindestens 28 Grad ist der Plan.

caption:
🌸 mùa hoa sưa về, Thủ đô Hà Nội

Cuối cùng thì mùa hoa sưa cũng trở lại với Thủ đô trên khắp các nẻo đường, trùng đợt với ngày 8/3 như tô thêm sự xinh đẹp cho chính ngày đặc biệt này. 

Lượn lờ vài góc phố, hoa nở trắng muốt, nếu mà cơn bão tháng 9 năm trước không càng quét thì mình tin mùa hoa sưa năm nay cũng đẹp hơn gấp bội lần.

Kể từ ngày dấn thân với niềm đam mê chụp ảnh, mình thuộc lòng các loài hoa, trước đó có đam mê hoa hiết gì đâu mà giờ đến mùa hoa nào là săn hoa đó, nhưng mà hoa đẹp thì mình cũng phải hướng về cái đẹp thôi.

8/3 chúc các chị em xinh đẹp rạng ngời, vui trẻ khoẻ khoắn, hạnh phúc và tràn ngập sự xinh đẹp nhé!

caption:
10 THINGS TO DO IN HANOI

The Ultimate Hanoi Bucket List! 🇻🇳✨

If you’re planning a trip to Hanoi, here are the absolute must-dos:

🌈 Rainbow Slide – Pure fun and adrenaline!

🚂 Train Street – Watch a train pass just inches away from you!

 ☕️ Rock King Coffee – A fairytale-like café you can’t miss.

🛶 Grand World – It looks like Venice, but it’s right here in Vietnam!

 🥖 Banh Mi 25 – The best Banh Mi in Hanoi, hands down.

 🛕 Thang Long Imperial Citadel – A stunning historic site full of culture.

🖼️ I Museum – A mesmerizing immersive art museum.

🏞️ Day Tour to Ninh Binh – One of the most breathtaking places in Northern Vietnam.

 👒 Quang Phu Cau – A vibrant incense village, perfect for Instagram-worthy shots.

 🗼Tran Quoc Pagoda – One of Hanoi’s most iconic landmarks.

caption:
Provando a crearmi una routine in questa vita da viaggiatrice full time. 🌀

A volte mi manca una stabilità e mi capita spesso di pensare “se fossi sempre a casa farei questo, quello e quell’altro”. Quando ci fermiamo per più di due giorni nello stesso posto stiamo provando a rallentare, anche se non è sempre così facile, dedicando metà giornata (o a volte tutta) a lavoro/e attività fisica e l’altra metà all’esplorazione.
Con un po’ di organizzazione si riesce a fare tutto! Mettere il mio benessere fisico e mentale al primo posto mi fa sentire più leggera 🤍

#hanoi #dailyvlog #vietnam #routine #viaggio #viaggi #viaggiare #travel
cleaned_caption: Trying to create a routine in this life from a full time traveler.Sometimes I miss a stability and I often think if I was always at home I would do this, that and that.When we stop for more than two days in the same place we are trying to slow down, even if it is not always that easy, dedicating half the day or sometimes all to work and physical activity and the half -praise half.With a little organization you can do everything!Putting my physical and mental well -being in the first place makes me feel lighter Hanoi dailyvlog Vietnam Routine Travel Travel Travel Travel

caption:
Eternal Motion: Hanoi’s Pulse

Lights streak past, bikes blur, and the streets are always alive. In Hanoi, life never slows down—it moves, rushes, and flows all day and night. As a photographer, I could sit in one spot and take 1,000 shots a day, and still, every moment would be different. There’s so much to see, so much to feel, so much to learn.

caption:
We would say one time is enough to experience the famous train street of Hanoi. However, going to the popular north end of the tracks was too stressful, so we wanted to give the south side a shot the next day. On the north side, there are police with barricades waving their hands and blowing their whistles if you try to walk down the street. The trick is that you need to wait at the entrance for a shop owner to invite you to their cafe. We felt like it was not a normal cafe where we wanted to enjoy our coffees for a little while, but instead felt rushed. There were people constantly walking up and down trying to sell everyone something making it feel even more like a tourist zoo. On top of that, our guide got into a long verbal fight with another shop owner and it was even more embarrassing for us to be there 🙈🙈 South side is the way to go—just google the cafe Hanoi 1990s for a reference of the area! The shop owners are friendly and easy going, and there is a lot more room to spread out and enjoy the Vietnamese coffees with a fun train encounter!
.
.

caption:
- List cafe Hà Nội 2025 số tiếp theo thì sẽ giới thiệu một quán cũng là nơi dừng chân của bạn Dean trong đợt về ăn Tết vừa rồi và đó chính là : "THE GARRISON - 41 Hồng Phúc, Ba Đình, Hà Nội."

Thật ra thì quán này là quán mà Dean đã đi từ năm 2024 nhưng mà đợt đó thì có những quán khác để dừng chân lâu hơn và cũng chưa có dịp giới thiệu cho mọi người biết nữa.

Quán thì cũng chả quá to mà đợt về Hà Nội lần này thì mình thích ngồi mấy quán đúng phong cách được ngồi outside, ngắm phố phường hơn là chui vào trong nhà ôm laptop như năm ngoái nữa. Ban đầu quán này mình còn nghĩ cho có mặt bằng ở đươi ai ngờ còn một vị trí trên tầng nữa mà mình còn chưa bao giờ lên đó luôn. 

Về đồ uống thì tất nhiên là mình sẽ đến đây chọn 2 loại đồ uống là Americano và Latte (nóng hay đá tuỳ tâm trạng). Cà phê thì không quá đậm nên với mình là sự lựa chọn ổn áp. Thường có những ngày mình ngồi đây thì khá chill và thoải mái vì outside cũng giới hạn vị trí ngồi thôi.

Anh em, bạn bè có thể đến đây trải nghiệm nhó.

#Hanoi #GocCuaDean #DeanRyun #Love #Life #Coffeetime #Photo #Iphone #TheGarrison
cleaned_caption: The next 2025 list of Cafe Cafe will introduce a shop that is also a place to stop Dean in the last Tet holiday and that is The Garrison 41 Hong Phuc, Ba Dinh, Hanoi.In fact, this restaurant is the shop that Dean has gone since 2024 but that time there are other shops to stop longer and have not had the opportunity to introduce to everyone anymore.The shop is not too big, but this time when I returned to Hanoi this time, I prefer to sit in the right style of the style to sit on the outside, watching the streets rather than going inside the house to hug the laptop like last year.Initially, this restaurant I thought about the premises in the unexpected place on the floor that I never went there.Regarding drinks, of course, I will come here to choose 2 types of drinks, Americano and hot latte or ice depending on the mood.Coffee is not too dark, so for me is a stabilized choice.Often there are days when I sit here, it is quite chill and comfortable because Outside also limits the seating position.Brothers and friends can come here to experience.Hanoi Goccuadean Deanryun Love Life Coffeetime Photo iPhone thegarrison

caption:
🥖

⬛︎Andersen Nordic Bakery

ベトナムに来てすぐに、近所のパン屋さん調べてその中で北欧系のハードパンを置いているお店を発見👀
だけど1人で外に行くのがハードル高すぎてここに行くまでに1ヶ月かかりました🔰
(タイホー区から出れない時期)

かぼちゃの種とひまわりの種と白ごま黒ごまがたくさん入ったパンが110k(≒660円)、大きいからハーフサイズがよかったのだけどできないとのこと…
でも別日に行ったらすでにハーフサイズがあって売ってくれました。はて？

白い丸いパンは10k(≒60円)で、レンジで温めるともちふわに！手に取ると意外に大きいしこれでこのお値段だなんて〜！

二つともおいしくてすごく私の好み！
最近行けてないけどまた行きたい〜
ライ麦とか使ってる系のパンをサワードウブレッドって呼ぶことを初めて知りました📝

イートインは少しだけ
ベビーカーでも一応入れる🙆‍♀️

—
りいさ🇯🇵(2024/09〜🇻🇳)

caption:
this was my FAVORITE meal from my entire two week Vietnam trip✨
 
one of the things I’ll miss most about Vietnam is the number of early options for food. Hanoi is known to be a bit chillier, so a hot noodle soup was exactly what I needed! one morning, my family found this stall serving one of my favorite meals of the entire trip. this dish is called Bún Ốc.

this dish is a sweet and tangy tomato based broth with vermicelli noodles and snails- yes snails! the literal translation to this dish is snail vermicelli 🥢 I got the special option which contains small and big size snails and their INCRED snail meatballs for $4 USD. note that it could even be $2, but I opted for the version with everythingggg. actually insane.

and for an early morning, it was popppping. you can get a seat at the main area, or there’s more seats across the street. preferably I love the low chairs and tables setting (true Vietnam experience) and I love the normalcy of having chilly pickled garlic that’s easily accessible on the table- lots of Vietnamese stalls do this 🧄🌶️

the owner there is the sweetest- she saw me recording and told me to come back when her pot was full of the snail meatballs (I would go back just for these) so I got some extra footage 😂

if you’re in Hanoi you NEED to check out this spot. if you’re a bit hesitant try the snails, get the snail meatballs instead (called chả)❣️

📍Bún Ốc Cô Huê
43 Nguyễn Siêu
Hanoi, Vietnam

more Vietnam recs on @viviandfoodie 🥰

Tokyo Red Grill
📍23 P. Phan Chu Trinh, Phan Chu Trinh, Hoàn Kiếm
※Sun Red River2階

・日替わりランチ　170k+
　今日は3色漬け丼でした🐟

本日コーナーストーンビル界隈で3件訪問。
JETROさんのアポアフター、向かいのサンレットリバーへ。
この界隈は公的機関や商社さんも多く入居されていますね。
Vetter時代に広告を頂いていたサンレットリバーさん。
東京レッドグリルさんもレストラン本に掲載頂いてました。

Tokyo Red Grillさんといえば
ハンバーグの乗ったオムライスや、メンチカツ
ステーキにハンバーグなどその名の通り洋食メニューがおすすめです！ボリューム満点。

今日の漬け丼も良かったけど、やっぱここは洋食メニュー推しかなあ。焼肉の乗った牛スパ気になりました。
丼は酢飯にしたのだけど、私には少し酢がきつかったかな？

今度はオムライスか牛スパ行ってみます。
サラダも副菜も丁寧で好きです。

caption:
📍Bai Dinh Pagoda / バイディン寺

The pagoda and temples complex is one of the largest Buddhist temples in Vietnam. It had 9 records includes the longest Arhat corridor in Asia (with 500 statues!), the largest bronze bell and the tallest statue. 
We visited there before sunset that I was looking for a beautiful view from 99-meter-tall Bao Thap tower. Somehow I went up twice though (don’t remember why), the view that unfolded before my eyes was wide and far-reaching, and the sun sinking over the horizon looked very small.

This complex is very large, and it is 800 meters from the base to the highest temple, and you have to climb 300 stone steps. But it’s mostly a gentle slope, and there is an electric car running within the site, so it wasn’t difficult to get around. We arrived in the evening, so there were few other tourists, and we enjoyed the illuminated temple after sunset before heading back.

ニンビン滞在中、時間足りなくていくつかパスした所もあるけど
ここはよかったなぁ。しかしとにかく広い。
夕方にサンセット目的で行ったけど、とんでもない所でしたわ。
他の観光客をほとんど見かけることなく、
閉園（？）ギリギリまでうろうろして、ライトアップ見てきた👏

実はこの日めちゃくちゃ疲れてたんやけど、
休憩所でおやつもらえるから！っていうアドバイスを頼りに
がんばって歩き回った🍬

📷 Sep/Oct 2024

caption:
Mais uma semana em Hanoi 🇻🇳

Descobrimos na cidade de Hanoi, a capital do Vietnam,  um dos shopping Center mais chique que já vimos 😱 tem academia, escritórios, supermercado e um aquário que é atração da cidade. Tudo no mesmo espaço! 

Continuamos nos deliciando com a comida vietnamita. Destaque para o Pho que é uma sopa com macarrão de arroz que é o prato icônico do Vietnam. Super recomendado! 😋😋

Se um dia vier ao Vietnam não deixe de provar os diferentes cafés e chás gelados. São deliciosos 😋😋

Apesar de caóticas, várias ruas são um charme 🥰🥰

E fomos assistir a um teatro de fantoches típico do Vietnã. Simplesmente seguimos apaixonados por esse país incrível. ❤️🇻🇳

caption:
🥩Top Rated A5 Wagyu Yakiniku in Viet Nam - Yazawa Ha Noi and Yazawa Sai Gon @yazawa.hanoi @yazawa.saigon 

For my meat lovers, this yakiniku restaurant serves A5 Wagyu Beef from Japan. Every course was melt in your mouth good, tender and so flavorful. It was truly the most tender cuts of beef I’ve ever had.

They serve it omakase style, meaning there’s a set menu selected by the chef or you can order from A la carte menu. The meat comes from all parts of the cow and their staff also grill the meat directly in front of you. My favorites were the Wagyu beef tarte, Yazawa yaki “sirloin”, and Chirasi box “A5 Marbled and lean wagyu, Ikura and scallop (from Hokkaido), lotus root, peas, egg, radish with vinegared rice”. 

Make sure to come hungry! 😋

caption:
Khi thành phố say giấc nồng 💭

Mùa nồm như một vị khách không mời, phủ lên mọi thứ lớp hơi ẩm dai dẳng. Sáng mở mắt thấy kính mờ sương, sàn nhà ướt sũng, quần áo mãi chả chịu khô.
Không khí như nặng trĩu, bám vào từng ngóc ngách, khiến người ta chỉ muốn cuộn mình trong chăn mà bỏ mặc cả thế giới ngoài kia. 

Nhưng giữa những ngày ẩm ướt ấy, phố phường lại có một vẻ đẹp rất riêng—những mái hiên lấp lánh nước, những cành cây đẫm sương, và mùi đất ẩm ngai ngái gợi về những ký ức xa xôi. Mùa nồm có thể làm người ta than thở, nhưng cũng chính nó khiến ta nhận ra rằng sau những ngày ẩm ướt, nắng lên lại quý giá đến nhường nào. -

caption:
Standing before the ancient Trấn Quốc Pagoda, I felt an overwhelming sense of peace. The red-brick stupa, the soft murmur of prayers, and the reflection of the temple in West Lake made me pause and truly soak in the moment.

As I walked through the pagoda grounds, I noticed an elderly woman lighting incense and bowing deeply in prayer. Out of curiosity, I approached her and, with a warm smile, she gestured for me to do the same. I followed her lead, closing my eyes, letting the scent of incense fill the air. For a brief moment, I wasn’t just a traveler—I felt connected to something greater, a universal sense of faith and gratitude.

This experience reminded me why I travel. It’s not just about seeing beautiful places but about the moments that change you—the unexpected connections, the quiet realizations, and the lessons that stay with you long after you leave.

Travel has a way of making us reach beyond ourselves, showing us how vast yet deeply connected this world is. ✨

caption:
I might just be manifesting a travel photography project. This is what I do, this is what I love.

When I was leaving Hanoi that morning, I knew in my heart, I wasn't ready to leave. But as we all are forced to do during hard good byes, I numbed my sadness and got on the cab to the airport. When I got there, my flight was nowhere to be listed. There was neither an email or any text informing me about the cancellation of the flight. Deep down, I could tell Hanoi wanted me to stay just one more day- One more day of aimless wandering. And that's exactly what I did. Some of my favourite shots from this series were made on the unexpected extra day I got in Hanoi. Thank you #Hanoi for being my selfless muse. 

Shot on #SonyA7c + 35mm 1.8

caption:
A collection of Hanoi as Lunar New Year approaches 🧧🌸

Being back in Hanoi for Lunar New Year ("Tết" in Vietnamese) for the first time in 5 years has been such a special experience for me. The city feels so alive: the streets filled with lanterns, national flags, festive decorations, the scent of traditional dishes wafting through the air, the occasional burst of peach blossoms and kumquat trees, and families bustling to prepare for the new year.

Enjoy this series of Hanoi captured over the past few days 🩷 I'm so grateful to be home for Tết this year. Wishing a joyful and prosperous Lunar New Year to all those who celebrate! 🐍🎇

📍1️⃣ Ban Công Cafe: A Hanoi gem, Ban Công (meaning "balcony") lives up to its popularity with one of the city’s most picturesque facades, always adorned with stunning seasonal decorations that make it a must-visit for café lovers
📍2️⃣3️⃣8️⃣ Train Street: An iconic Hanoi experience where life bustles inches away from the train tracks, offering an unforgettable mix of local charm and vibrant energy
📍4️⃣ Tạ Hiện Street: Known as “Beer Street,” Tạ Hiện is Hanoi’s nightlife hub, always buzzing with life and celebration
📍5️⃣ One Pillar Pagoda: A symbol of Hanoi’s spiritual heritage, this pagoda, perched on a single stone pillar, is as captivating in its design as it is in its history
📍7️⃣ Ancient House - 87 Mã Mây Street: A beautifully preserved slice of Hanoi’s history, this 19th-century house offers a glimpse into traditional Vietnamese architecture and living

📌 Save and follow @julieythe1st for more travel tips!

caption:
🎠 5 cosas que no sabías sobre Hong Kong Disneyland‼️ 

😱 Es el parque Disney más pequeño del mundo y el que tiene menos afluencia de todos. Fue el segundo en abrir en Asia y este año celebra su 20 aniversario. 

🏰 Originalmente abrió sus puertas con un Castillo que era una copia exacta del Castillo de la Bella Durmiente de Disneyland California pero hace unos años decidieron demoler parte de ese castillo y construir uno nuevo sobre sus cimientos dando lugar al “Castle of Magical Dreams” un espectacular castillo único en el mundo dedicado a todas las princesas Disney 

👻 Para adaptarse al público local tuvieron que crear una versión única de “The Haunted Mansion” llamada “Mystic Manor” ya que en China no tiene sentido tenerle miedo a los fantasmas ya que allí los antepasados son venerados

☃️ Cuenta con el primer reino de Arendelle que abrió en un parque Disney y es el único que por ahora tendrá dos atracciones, siendo hasta la fecha la mejor y más completa zona de Frozen que existe.

🎢 Tiene una zona de Toy Story que es una copia exacta a la de París pero en cambio la zona del oeste es completamente diferente, ya que en lugar de llamarse Frontierland la han llamado Grizzly Glunch y en lugar de tener la atracción Big Thunder Mountain cuenta con otra totalmente diferente llamada Big Grizzly Mountain.

caption:
A tale of buildings. In many parts of the world, private life remains private—the notions of home and intimacy tucked away neatly behind houses with front lawns, drowned out by television white noise or the whir of a washing machine.

In densely-populated cities, though, private life tends to run out of space; it has little choice but to protrude from windows & ram past the sound barrier of thin walls. When I see laundry in Hong Kong being set to hang dry in the morning, I’m reminded of the depth of life that’s so often out of view.

There’s something strangely comforting about it—the shirts and towels flapping in the wind, the wandering sounds of luncheon meat and choy sum fried in oil. A reassurance that I am accompanied in this world; the thought that in another life, that home may well have been my own.

caption:
香港 at night. 🖤 Returning places is like holding up a mirror—at least, that’s the way it’s always been for me. All the familiar parts of you embrace familiar places; all the parts of you that have changed feel alienated or out of place.

I think that’s why there’s a lot of complexity in how I feel about Hong Kong. It’s immensely fulfilling to be in the place that formed my first years of discovering touch and smell. My earliest memories are baked into those tall glasses of iced lemon tea, twinkling skyscraper lights, and humidity eating away at the apartment walls.

But there’s no doubt it also brings me sorrow. I pass wet markets, piled with fresh fish that I don’t possess the know-how to buy. I see the whirring fan of my aunt’s apartment and remember all the journal entries I wrote beneath it one summer; all the ways I was different, and in many respects unrecognizable, to the person I am today.

Without points of reference, you don’t truly know how you’ve changed. Returning somewhere reminds us time marches on. Someday we’ll exhaust the years we have on this planet, and someday the generations-old restaurant across the street will shut its doors, and someday we’ll think about that place for the last time. I want a life full of returns—a life of reminders that time isn’t infinite.

caption:
AUTOMA

AUTOMA by Martin Massé
Table
Limited Edition of 12
Satin Wedge
H 29.5  W 114.1  D 39.3 in
H 75  W	290  D 100 cm
Paris

The Automa collection by Martin Massé explores the ancestral art of stacking, where geometric forms—rectangular prisms, spheres, and cylinders—interlock in compositions that evoke both balance and tension. Referencing the totems of early civilizations and the rock cairns that have guided travelers since prehistoric times, Massé’s collection translates these archetypal structures into a contemporary design language. Each work oscillates between solidity and precariousness, engaging the viewer in a dialogue between gravity and equilibrium.

The collection’s formal clarity is animated by a playful approach to structure. Automa recalls the intuitive logic of childhood building games, where shapes and volumes are assembled through an instinctive sense of composition. This interplay of precision and spontaneity draws from the legacy of the Memphis movement, particularly the work of Ettore Sottsass, known for his architectonic compositions and dynamic superimpositions. Here, Massé refines these influences into a more restrained and essentialist vision, distilling the expressive potential of stacked forms while maintaining a rigorously minimal aesthetic.

Each material is essential to the collection’s sense of play, mystery, and warmth. The rich depth of stained wenge wood, finished with a satin varnish, lends a timeless sophistication to the whimsical compositions. Upholstery in understated Kvadrat virgin wool introduces a quiet tactile contrast to the bold geometric volumes. The collection’s monolithic bench, sculpted from Rosso Luana marble, anchors the series with its richly colored veining and geological exuberance.

Handcrafted in France, each work is crafted with exceptional precision, underscoring the inherent tension between mass and lightness, structure and play. In limited editions of twelve, the Automa collection transforms elementary forms into a study of equilibrium, celebrating humanity’s timeless need to play and create meaning.

STUDIOTWENTYSEVEN
New York Gallery
241 Church Street, New York, NY
By Appointment Only

caption:
📌樂樂韓式豬手 (深水埗)
深水埗欽州街37K號西九龍中心8樓美食廣場8F77-79號舖

佢地開係西九龍中心美食廣場入面
雖然店面細細 但人氣好高 價錢又唔貴
今次我就嗌左幾樣食物❤️

🔹蒜蓉豬手 (半份)
豬手燉得軟爛入味 有大量蒜蓉鋪面
蒜香味勁濃郁 膠質豐富 
食落黏嘴但又好滿足
半份分量啱啱好 適合兩個人分享😋

🔹玫瑰卡邦尼年糕
韓式年糕同義式卡邦尼醬結合
醬汁濃郁帶少少甜味 所以唔會太辣
年糕Q彈有咬口 配料仲有魚糕tim❤️

🔹原味飯卷
飯卷用料十足 有黃瓜、胡蘿蔔、菠菜、醃蘿蔔
米飯軟硬適中 內餡雖然簡單但好味
可以品嚐到食材嘅原味😍

🔹吞拿魚飯卷
吞拿魚搭配美乃滋同蔬菜
口感豐富 味道清爽
份量都幾多 食晒都幾飽肚👏🏻

caption:
3D2N at Hong Kong Disneyland Hotel and one whole day in Disneyland is full with joys and my inner child tak boleh tahan seeing my favourite characters. 
Here are some reference and cost for those yang plan nak pergi HK Disneyland for 3 days:
1. Ada 3 hotel nearby yang ada shuttle. (HK Disneyland Hotel, Explorer’s Lodge and Disney Hollywood) RM1100-2000~ per night
2. Install Hong Kong Disneyland apps and purchase
- Entry ticket
- Early entry pass (ni wajib baru puas dapat main semua tanpa beratur sebab dapat masuk satu jam awal)
- 8 Attractions Premier Access ( priority access tanpa beratur)
- Dinner Buffet + “Momentous” Special Viewing area (ni wajib untuk dapat view best masa night show pukul 8pm)
- few others Premier Access can purchase on the spot to avoid long queue and save your time. 
3. Halal food and restaurant easy to find
I spent about RM1k for premier access in Disneyland for one person not include the hotel. 
Overall, kalau beli premier access is worthy. If not, you cant complete the rides and show in one day. HK disneyland is smallest among others Disneyland, but wear proper attire and bring your umbrella too👍
#hongkongdisneyland #hongkong #hongkongdisneylandhotel

Install Hong Kong Disneyland apps and purchase Entry ticket Early entry pass ni wajib baru puas dapat main semua tanpa beratur sebab dapat masuk satu jam awal 8 Attractions Premier Access priority access tanpa beratur Dinner Buffet Momentous Special Viewing area ni wajib untuk dapat view best masa night show pukul 8pm few others Premier Access can purchase on the spot to avoid long queue and save your time. 3. Halal food and restaurant easy to find I spent about RM1k for premier access in Disneyland for one person not include the hotel. Overall, kalau beli premier access is worthy. If not, you cant complete the rides and show in one day. 跟配的芫荽尖椒醬食用感更清爽！

-🐮和牛沙巴當 / $198

-🍚葱香月見飯 / $28
吃燒肉必配飯吧！香蔥帶點微辣可以消消油膩感～

-🍹焦糖菠蘿乳酸 / $38

乳酸很解膩！

caption:
A pocket of peace worth visiting 🥹

📍 Tai O

To get here, you have to take Bus 11 from Tung Chung MTR station. This isn’t my first time there, but every time I come here I find myself loving the rich culture this village presents because it’s a very different side of Hong Kong worth learning about and appreciating.

You immediately feel how much the residents love this village. They pour so much into it. And that’s why I love coming here 🤍

〰️ Fishball from the first stall into the village 
〰️ @taiobakery (Mango Mochi)
〰️ @_solocafe (Coffee + Light Bites)
〰️ @chamberfairy (Essential Oil blends)
〰️ Wen’s Store (Adorable Gift Shop)
〰️ Ching Kee (Tofu pudding)
〰️ Venice Seafood Restaurant (Squid with Shrimp Paste)

caption:
This ancient town is something we wished we had visited before! Exceptionally well-preserved with its wooden houses built on stilts along the Tuo River, Fenghuang is showcasing traditional Ming and Qing architectural styles, definitely one of the highlight of our Hunan trip. 

Fenghuang’s (鳳凰古城,fènghuáng gǔchéng) history dates back over 1,300 years and js known for its rich cultural heritage, including the Miao and Tujia ethnic minorities.

For those coming from Hong Kong you can even take the high speed train to visit it! 🚝

📍Fenghuang, Hunan, China

Follow @travelailleurs for more adventures! ✨

Skyscrapers and vertical labyrinths are Hong Kong’s way of writing poetry and dreams into the sky. This giant cosmopolitan city never ceases to amaze me with its the vibrant culture and dynamic pace. caption:
•новости такси•

Ну наконец-то свершилось!
То, с чего начинается любое путешествие для туриста- ТАКСИ!

Гонконг готовится к революции в сфере услуг такси: уже к концу этого месяца на дорогах появятся еще 3500 такси, включая 1900 электромобилей.

Это произошло после того, министр транспорта и логистики Mable Chan объявила о запуске пяти лицензированных таксомоторных парков города.
Она подчеркнула важность инноваций в секторе такси, который в последние годы столкнулся с многочисленными проблемами.

Думаю тут вы согласитесь, что в Гонконге большая проблема с такси, чаще они очень старые, грязные и водители не самые вежливые ребята Гонконга 😅

В новом автопарке будут представлены как электрические, так и гибридные автомобили, а также транспортные средства, доступные для инвалидных колясок. Приблизительно 1500 такси будут совершенно новыми, а оставшиеся автомобили будут младше трех лет.

Каждое транспортное средство будет оснащено передовыми функциями безопасности, включая системы GPS, видеорегистраторы и системы мониторинга водителя, а также возможностью электронной оплаты.

Маленькими шажками в современный мир такси🤩
cleaned_caption: Taxi news, well, finally happened!What starts any trip for a tourist taxi!Hong Kong is preparing for a revolution in the field of taxi services by the end of this month on the roads another 3,500 taxi will appear, including 1900 electric vehicles.This happened after the Minister of Transport and Logistics Mable Chan announced the launch of five licensed taxi parks of the city.She emphasized the importance of innovation in a taxi sector, which in recent years has encountered numerous problems.I think here you will agree that Hong Kong is a big problem with a taxi, more often they are very old, dirty and drivers are not the most polite guys of Hong Kong in the new fleet of both electric and hybrid cars, as well as vehicles available for invalid strollers.About 1,500 taxis will be completely new, and the remaining cars will be younger than three years.Each vehicle will be equipped with advanced security functions, including GPS systems, DVRs and driver monitoring systems, as well as the possibility of electronic payment.Small steps in the modern world of taxi

caption:
呢間嘅川菜真係又抵食又好味😋CP值極高👍🏻

香辣魚皮香脆可口，鮮香滿溢，雖然對於我黎講都真係幾辣下，但又好食到唔想停

金湯酸菜魚揀咗唔辣，不過佢原本個湯底都有10小辣，好啱唔食得辣嘅我😊，魚肉口感嫩滑，🈶菇、萵筍片、蘿蔔片、薯粉等配料，十分惹味

片皮鴨揀咗半隻，有🔟片麼麼皮，夠薄又唔會易穿，片皮鴨選用肥瘦適中嘅鴨肉，經過烤製後外皮酥脆，肉質香滑，搭配青瓜條、蔥絲➕甜醬一齊食，感覺好滿足

呢度嘅紅糖糍粑炸得剛剛好，外層微酥，內裡軟糯，點上香濃嘅紅糖汁，香甜而不膩

飲品揀咗桃之天夭➕凍檸樂，前者以桃嘅香甜為基調，搭配清新嘅氣泡感梳打及粒粒寒天，好啱我口味， 後者酸甜解膩，飲落好清爽

Hi JISOO see u in Hong Kong & Macau in March!! 🤩🤩🤩

韓國人氣天后 JISOO 《JISOO ASIA FAN TOUR 2025: ”LIGHTS, LOVE, ACTION!“》香港及澳門站

韓國人氣女團 BLACKPINK 成員 JISOO 早前推出新迷你專輯〈AMORTAGE〉，主打曲目 〈earthquake〉火速登上 Billboard《世界數位歌曲銷售榜》第 1 位，更在全球 45 個地區的 iTunes 專輯榜及中國騰訊音樂綜合 K-POP 榜上達到第一名。JISOO 近日更正式宣布，將於中國澳門及中國香港 舉行個人亞洲巡迴粉絲見面會——JISOO《ASIA FAN TOUR 2025: ”LIGHTS, LOVE, ACTION!“》，與粉絲們近距離見面。日期為 3 月 21 日至 22 日於中國澳門銀河綜藝館(Galaxy Arena) ，以及 3 月 28 日至 29 日於中國香港亞洲國際博覽館 Arena 舉行。JISOO 對此次巡演充滿期待，表示很開心能夠再次與中國澳門和中國香港的粉絲見面！具體的詳細內容及售票資訊將會陸續公布，請密切留意官方消息以獲取最新資訊！下星期香港開始售票，有關詳情請大家留意 Klook!

《JISOO ASIA FAN TOUR 2025: ”LIGHTS, LOVE, ACTION!“》 Hong Kong & Macau Stops

BLACKPINK member and K-pop sensation JISOO has recently released her new mini-album 〈AMORTAGE〉, with the title track 〈earthquake〉 skyrocketing to No. 1 on Billboard’s World Digital Song Sales Chart. The album has also dominated the iTunes Album Charts in 45 countries worldwide and secured the top spot on Tencent Music’s comprehensive K-POP Chart in China. JISOO has now officially announced her Asia Fan Tour 2025: ”LIGHTS, LOVE, ACTION!“, where she will meet fans up close in Macau and Hong Kong. The tour dates are as follows:

March 21-22 – Galaxy Arena, Macau
March 28-29 – AsiaWorld-Expo Arena, Hong Kong

Expressing her excitement, JISOO shared that she is thrilled to reunite with her fans in Macau and Hong Kong. Further details, including ticketing information, will be announced soon. Stay tuned for official updates and Hong Kong will start the Tickets sales next week with Klook!

caption:
📍Le Menu @gloucesterlukkwok 

上個weekend去咗灣仔六國酒店嘅Le Menu食buffet🍽️而家主題係[華麗盛宴•自助晚餐] 有鮑魚/鵝肝/扣鮑魚等等 最特別係每晚都有即場烹調示範👨🏻‍🍳[堂弄原隻鮑魚鴨掌][法式龍蝦海鮮酥皮盒]同埋[火焰雪山] 互動氣氛都唔錯啊🥰三款中我最鐘意鮑魚鴨掌 好入味yum yum
食物種類都算豐富✨
冷盤區域 有幾款沙律/ham/salami 特式啲嘅有煙鮫魚同豬肉凍批 而大部分人最關心嘅凍海鮮 龍蝦/螺/麵包蟹/青口/蝦/長腳蟹共6款🦞都好新鮮而且fill得好密 刺身同壽司少不了 款式就大路款 勝在新鮮同埋都夠厚切🍣
食完凍嘢食熱嘢🥢
熱盤選擇有二十幾款 有驚喜 亦有唔少海鮮呢💕我嘅必食推介 燒比目魚配布根地紅酒汁/芝士蘑菇焗蟹蓋/蒜蓉粉絲蒸扇貝/椒鹽大蝦/京醬骨 特別留意龍蝦海鮮茶碗蒸 蒸蛋入面有嘅唔係龍蝦碎 係大大件龍蝦肉‼️如果鍾意飲湯嘅 有款花膠瑤柱羹湯好足料~而燒烤區域就有燒肉眼扒同埋片皮鵝🪿
食完鹹嘢食甜嘢🍰
甜品都多款式 賣相都靚㗎 尤其是芒果慕絲蛋糕🥭而且呢度嘅甜品係喺雪櫃入面 由職員幫你攞 唔洗怕比人摷到亂晒😂每一件都靚靚仔仔
環境優雅 服務又好 如果家人或朋友gathering想食buffet 呢度係個好選擇

由葡萄牙主廚坐鎮，開左有接近16年嘅正宗葡國菜餐廳✨ 之前試過佢哋嘅Brunch質素唔錯，而最近推出嘅任食葡式烤乳豬 + 傳統葡式飯 8道菜早午餐，真係超吸引！講緊之前單點烤乳豬都要$390，依家無限追加也太幸福了吧!!! 仲要入座即送葡萄牙綠酒/佩爾塞雞尾酒一杯，咁先係Weekend要嘅態度😎

< 𝗗𝗘𝗦𝗦𝗘𝗥𝗧𝗦 >

caption:
This is the longest I’ve been home, and only for the second time, since 2018. 

As someone who is head over heels for my career, I often find it really hard to part ways with my NYC life—I constantly need to be doing “something” or feel like I’m missing out if I’m not there.

I learned that your career doesn’t become less important, but other things start to matter more. Everything has its time and its place. Everything is temporary. Time truly is precious and irreplaceable.

And that includes time with your parents. While I was home, I got to do so many healing things with them. I got to know their stories and support them in a way I didn’t know how to before. We laughed a lot and cried even more.

I also got to eat a lot of good food, so much that I got food poisoning last week bahahah. It was so awful—my tastebuds have changed sadly. I’m triggered by seafood and raw fish now…WHO AM I 💀 

I got to hang out with my childhood friends who were also in Hong Kong, giggling like our teenage years again, reminiscing the past and excited for our future dreams. These friendships are magic.

At the same time I still went in for some massive auditions! NYC in a funny way kept pulling me back energetically, but I no longer feel like I’m missing out.

This trip was a soul-opening one. Time truly is precious and irreplaceable.

NYC, see you soon 🖤

〰️ unedited by @maison_creo
photographers @joeyyuen @ctkkit_photography

caption:
銅鑼灣 ｜ 板神鉄板燒日本料理 

知道板神慶祝五週年推出優惠，立即約朋友過來銅鑼灣店品嚐一下，店內環境寬敞，以廂房式設計，每房可容納4-8人不等💫

坐下來更驚喜發現每位由$555 就嘗試到 ，絕對讓你稱心滿意💫

鐵板燒十五品 $555/位起

💢追加 
帆立貝 加$68
火焰北寄貝 $128

五週年鉄板燒套餐（一位） 基本上套餐包括以下所有食物，按牛肉產地區分價錢，自由選擇，套餐以外亦可追加生蠔、刺生等，總之務求食客吃過夠💫

▪️前菜
時合蔬菜沙律、大根蘿蔔、刺身
沙律清新可口，面頭佈滿炸春卷皮絲，配上甘旬汁，新鮮爽脆；刺身有三款，肥美新鮮💫

▪️南非飽魚
非常新鮮生猛，簡單以鐵板處理，原味入口解嫩，亦可沾點醬汁拌吃，但原味已很足夠，新嫩彈牙💫

▪️西班牙紅蝦伴天使麵
廚師先將日式天使麵油炸，炸後酥脆可口，再加上爽彈的西班牙紅蝦及獨家秘製醬汁，食時連麵蝦汁一同吃，味道層次非常豐富💫

▪️帶子
簡單香煎兩邊，外層焦香，中間嫩滑彈牙，而且非常鮮味💫

▪️牛舌芯
牛舌芯煙韌有咬口，入口爽脆多汁💫

▪️鵝肝
以小漢堡🍔夾上鵝肝，整個放入口非常美味💫

▪️和牛A5薄燒（$755）
以5成熟處理，恰到好處，中間包裹着大量炸蒜跟蔥粒口感非常豐富💫

▪️厚燒（$805）
同樣以5成熟處理，外層微焦，中間保持嫩滑有肉汁，味道一絕💫

▪️炒飯
米飯粒粒分明，配上雞蛋、牛肉碎、蔥、紅蘿蔔、洋蔥，配料非常豐富💫

▪️野菜
翠玉瓜，杏鮑菇、紅椒、粟米芯，爽脆多汁💫

▪️湯 - 麵豉湯
▪️甜品 - 香蕉煎餅、抹茶奶凍
香蕉煎餅外脆內軟、抹茶奶茶香滑味美💫

caption:
《 上環斜巷西班牙菜🇪🇸 》

一向鍾意上環新舊交集既感覺，巷仔轉角都隱藏住好多美食🥰今次就去到西街既西班牙菜El vaso de oro，店面佈置同室外座位充滿外國氛圍，牆上一格格色彩繽紛瓷磚亦好有地道西班牙感覺 🇪🇸 餐牌上小吃、冷熱Tapas及主菜一應俱全，7點前仲有好抵飲既happy hour menu，好適合同朋友放工飲返杯🥂

🔸 Bikini – Iberico Ham and Melted Cheese Sandwich with Black Truffle
最愛tapas之一✨兩片麵包夾住伊比利亞火腿及芝士，再塗滿厚厚黑松露醬，用牛油煎香後半溶芝士口感軟滑，火腿鹹香配上黑松露獨有香氣，食唔停口🤤
🔸 Classic Wagyu Beef Tartare with Toast
每間餐廳生牛肉他他都有不同風味，呢度嘅生牛肉、酸瓜同洋蔥比例適宜，簡單調味帶出肉香😍旁邊仲有香蔥牛油，加少少入牛肉他他更能提升風味，最適合放上脆多士一齊食！
🔸Homemade Chicken & Duck Liver Pate
自家製雞鴨肝醬口感綿密幼滑，仲附上麵包片可以一齊食；最特別係旁邊附上西瓜蓉，清新甜味平衡肝醬膩感，係好有心思既食材配搭🥰
🔸Croquette of the day
今日既味道係蘑菇，內餡幼滑薯蓉及蘑菇粒調味恰好，炸至金黃之後做到外脆內軟完美口感🥳鍾意croquette可以逐件落單，唔夠喉都可以單點多幾件！
🔸Padron Peppers
每次食西班牙菜必點既小青椒，煎香後簡單用鹽調味已經能帶出青椒本身香氣，送酒必點🍺

Always loved Sheung wan for its mix of culture and the alleys to explore – this time we’ve found this gem on Sai Street! El vaso de oro offers a range of Spanish tapas and mains, in a laid-back setting with both counters and tables. Great for a night out with friends🥂

🔸Bikini – Iberico Ham and Melted Cheese Sandwich with Black Truffle
Grilled sandwiches of iberico ham, cheese and black truffle sauce, loved the gooey melted cheese along with savory iberico ham, complimented by the signature fragrance of black truffle!🤤
🔸Classic Wagyu Beef Tartare with Toast
Balanced flavors of raw wagyu beef, onion and pickles, served with some butter and scallion on the side which surprisingly enhanced the flavor of tartare!
🔸Homemade Chicken & Duck Liver Pate
Liver pate was rich and smooth on palate, and we loved how the chef chose to serve some watermelon puree on the side – it was a perfect companion to balance out the heaviness of pate!🍉

caption:
The long, steep streets of Hong Kong are uniquely fascinating, as the density of commerce and daily life unfolds upon them. Hong Kong Island is dominated by a massive mountain, Victoria Peak. The steep slopes, dense forests and rocky terrain present immense challenges, yet this monster city has managed to carve out roads, tunnels and entire neighborhoods into the mountainside. The engineering ingenuity and tenacity of the people are truly a marvel to admire. 💚

受東北季候風影響，本港昨晚（3.5）氣溫驟降，一夜急跌8℃，今早（3.6）多區氣溫降至12℃或以下，其中大老山僅9.1℃，市區最低約14℃。大埔、上水等新界地區則跌至13℃左右，全港普遍較昨日低約6℃。今日最高氣溫僅17℃，晚間北風增強，離岸及高地陣風明顯。 

天文台預測，今晚（3.6）至明早氣溫將進一步下降，新界部分地區持續寒冷，呼籲市民注意保暖，並關顧長者及慢性病患者。

未來兩日天氣持續清涼，明日（3.7）市區最低溫約13℃，新界寒冷。周六（3.8）起氣溫緩慢回升，周末至下周初（3.9-11）最高溫升至21-25℃，天色轉晴。然而，下周三（3.13）起將迎潮濕天氣，海洋氣流帶來大霧及微雨，連續三日相對濕度達100%，能見度或顯著降低。 

近期困擾市民的“回南天”因冷空氣暫時消退，但下周中後期潮濕氣流重返，衣物難乾問題可能再現。周末回暖期間，日夜溫差可達6-8℃，近期氣溫波動大，V仔建議大家，及時調整衣物，並留意長者健康。

caption:
青海源地直送・味遊中國‼️

香港身為美食大都會，要吃什都都輕而易舉，今日就相約朋友，品嘗來自青海高原直送的食材養生晚餐💫

青海位於高海拔高度，原始有機無污染嘅生態環境，將氂牛、藏羊、三文魚(虹鱒)、藜麥、枸杞、冬蟲夏草等等青海獨有食材直送到餐廳，透過粵菜烹調手法炮製出一系列限定佳餚，絕對不能錯過💫

💢掛爐蜜味藏羊排
青海黑藏羊屬高原型藏羊，平日食的羊排都是以燒為主，這裡的羊排以掛爐燒，外層份外焦香，酥脆可口，肉質好嫩，中間帶有少少膏位，羊味重，但不會太羶💫

💢有機藜麥氂牛肉羹
新鮮的氂牛肉有嚼勁，但不會有渣，用來煮湯羹絕對很可以，牛味相對更見鮮味，再配上健康的藜麥，藜麥耐寒耐旱，最愛海拔高，口味絕對配搭💫

💢雞樅菌露筍炒氂牛柳
雞樅菌菇味濃郁，爽口又多汁，配上爽脆露筍，口感層次豐富，用來炒氂牛柳，可以更帶出牛肉味道，青海氂牛遊走終年積雪的高山崇嶺，一生大量攝入蟲草、雪蓮等天然藥用植物，高蛋白，低脂肪，肉質有嚼勁，絕對美味之作💫

💢避風塘青海三文魚 (虹鱒)扒
龍羊峽虹鱒魚是青海著名水 產，肉質細膩有嚼勁、脂肪含量較高，以避風塘造法烹調三文魚，非常有創意，青海三文魚歸類虹鱒，口感嫩滑，油脂比較豐盈，令人回味💫

💢枸杞魚湯水耕生菜
青海枸杞大粒又甘甜，魚湯以枸杞加入水耕生菜，把菜浸熟，帶出青海枸杞及生菜的清甜💫

💢祁連黃菇氂牛肉酥餅
「青海十寶」美譽的祁連黃菇，菇味比較濃，用來做牛肉酥餅加添陣陣菇香，外皮香酥，内餡鲜嫩，牛味濃郁 💫

💢高原枸杞桂圓糕
鮮紅飽滿的青海枸杞，加入安心養神的桂圓、雪棗製成凍糕，吃起來不僅口感甜蜜美味，更可滋補養顏💫

🌟想試清海食材菜式，要把握機會🌟

caption:
AUTHENTIC CHINESE DISHES IN THE HEART OF SHEFFIELD 🥢

This signature Hong Kong restaurant is serving up some of the most authentic dishes with a modern twist. 

@cha_ting_sheffield has everything from all kinds of noodle dishes, delicious salt and pepper plates, and juicy satay chicken skewers, all carefully created by their dedicated chefs who’re all from Hong Kong. 🍜

They have loads of offers on too, like a free starter when you order any two glasses of beer or wine, or their weekday meal deal which is chicken curry or crispy chilli beef and a free drink for just £12, Monday to Friday 12-5pm. 🍷

Open every day except Tuesday, from 12-10pm. 

📍Where to find them: 124 Devonshire Street, S3 7SF

caption:
One of the oldest Cha chaan teng, HK diners, in Hong Kong! 

📍 Ho Wah Restaurant (Wan Chai)
226 Johnston Road, Wan Chai

The older looking stall is their original location and the newer location opened in 2013. All the food still comes from the kitchen of their original location =)

I participated in a tour organised by @hongkonghistoricalshops which was organised into 2 parts. One to learn more about the restaurant and the second half to try making milk tea yourselves. I believe this tour runs about once a month however, the tour is conducted in Cantonese.

caption:
Why would you move back to HK? 🇭🇰 

I’ve been asked this question so many times, especially at a time when so many are wanting to leave. But it just makes sense at this point of our lives. Three main reasons:
1. Raising a kid without a village while working full time is hard. Being back in HK allows us to have a support network with family and hired help.
2. Culture and identity is really important to me. I want to make sure my son speaks Cantonese (yes incl swear words) and is in touch with his culture.
3. It’s soooo much easier to travel overseas from HK compared to Australia, where it’s considered normal to fly 24 hours to get somewhere 🥲

Plus all the reasons that make HK awesome like food, activities, public transport, convenience, efficiency, mix of city and nature etc etc etc… 

#hongkong #香港 #relocation

caption:
✨歲月留香展覽✨ 粵菜文化嘅奇妙旅程😍

當日參加咗 東南樓 - 歲月留香展覽，真係好開心又好有得著！🎉 一入到展覽就好似穿越時光隧道，回到1950-1990年代嘅香港，感受到嗰陣粵菜嘅傳奇故事同文化變遷🍲✨。東南樓從一間普通茶樓開始，到成為著名嘅海鮮酒家，真係睇到香港飲食文化點樣隨住時代進步～👏

「點心蒸籠小盆栽工作坊」真係超有趣😍，用迷你嘅蒸籠整個小盆栽，再加上點心擺設，成品又靚又有特色🌱！仲有幸收到久作大師 @9_drawing 親筆為我創作嘅詩句，將詩詞寫喺蒸籠上面，真係好有意境呀～❤️ 完全係專屬嘅回憶！📸

最後仲喺展覽入面食住港式點心睇展覽🥢，一邊感受粵菜文化嘅歷史，一邊欣賞東南樓嘅藝術同故事，真係別有一番滋味～🤩

👋 快啲去參加啦！
📍展覽係 #免費 入場，仲可以喺官網報名參加 「點心蒸籠小盆栽工作坊」 或 「詩詞書法體驗」～💡 
📅 展覽由 2月22日至5月22日，機會難得唔好錯過！🔥

🔗 詳情睇呢度 👉 [https://www.tungnamlou.com/tw/taste-of-time-exhibition.html](https://www.tungnamlou.com/tw/taste-of-time-exhibition.html) 

📍地址：油麻地砵蘭街68號東南樓藝術酒店 (油麻地港鐵A1出口） 
⏰ 開放時間：星期一至日，10:00AM – 6:00PM

caption:
近日，一名本港女性乘坐國泰航空航班飛往台灣，在機上更換SIM卡時，不慎將香港SIM卡滑落，導致跌在兩張座椅中間。在乘客全數離機後，機組人員協同工程師拆解座椅結構，耗時近半小時終尋回卡片。當事人在社交平台發文致謝，稱“若非機組專業態度恐難尋回”，事件隨即引發網絡熱議。

網民們紛紛表示，建議樓主給國泰航空法電郵表揚“佢哋係會加分的，亦都多謝你”、“麻煩send email去表揚”，但亦有人呼籲乘客不應在航機上換SIM卡，“空中服務員見得最多就係你呢啲情況，亦都係最討厭嘅情況之一”、“阻人收工”。

據航空業內人士透露，此類“非安全類個案”處理需動用3-5名機組人員，涉及延誤清潔班次、影響後續航班準備等隱形成本。國泰機組主動介入的服務意識值得肯定，但事件亦折射現代航空業的兩難：乘客對個性化服務的期待，與航空公司運營效率間的平衡。
 
此事件猶如微型棱鏡，折射出航空服務業在適應性上的挑戰。或許我們更需建立一種共同體意識：既珍視服務業者的專業付出，亦恪守乘客的責任邊界。對此，你點睇？

caption:
期待明天❣️終於到我大日子啦❣️

終於終於 明天正式成為人妻了(ღˇ◡ˇ)
真的緊張到不得了 要踏入人生新階段啦

希望事事順利 陽光普照☀️
搞得好好睇睇 全世界開開心心🥰

回顧我的𝟗輯𝐏𝐫𝐞 𝐖𝐞𝐝𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠
最令我們印象深刻的是 白川鄉的結婚照呀💓

男朋友在白川鄉跟我求婚
所以我好想好想 重回白川鄉拍婚紗照呀～

我們都是日本愛好者
我真的好想穿正裝和服去日本婚攝呀 ˃̣̣̥᷄⌓˂̣̣̥᷅

沒想到 我非常幸運♥️
抽中@d_weddingphoto_hk的婚攝大獎👑
當時 真 的 超 級 興 奮‼️有 美 夢 成 真 的 感 覺‼️

拍出來的效果實在太好了 所以要好好推薦一下🤣

ꔚ 日本婚攝公司 日本國內分別有𝟐𝟓個𝐒𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐨分佈各地
  拍攝地點日子可按照個人旅程事前議定 超貼心
ꔚ 前一天去附近𝐒𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐨試身 不需帶衫 非常方便!!
ꔚ 日本攝影師&化妝師團隊 職人精神 一絲不苟
ꔚ 日本攝影師 會先去𝐬𝐢𝐭𝐞 𝐯𝐢𝐬𝐢𝐭 預定可行路線
ꔚ 日本化妝師全程跟妝 還懂得幫我和服呢👘
ꔚ 香港翻譯全程陪同 溝通完全沒問題👌🏻

我只能說 日本團隊真的零舍不同😌
換衣服時會帶同地氈 不用我的腳踏在冷冰冰的地上
知道是拍雪景 會預先準備一大堆暖暖包&羽絨🥹
連羽絨都有耶 也 太 貼 心 了 吧🥹🥹🥹～

而更令我感動的是
每次一拍照完 每個人都會馬上衝過來給我暖暖包&大羽絨
明明我在雪中拍攝 基乎長期都是暖的狀態🥰
當初還以為拍雪景會好辛苦 沒想到如此溫暖(ꈍᴗꈍ) 

真 心 推 薦 呀❤️‍🔥

🇭🇰I was invited to the Hyatt Centric in Hong Kong and visited North Point. Unlike Tsim Sha Tsui, North Point has a unique charm, and I had a great time there.

The daytime view from the Hyatt Centric is stunning, and the night view is even more breathtaking. The staff are incredibly friendly, making it the most memorable hotel I’ve stayed at in Hong Kong.

Make sure not to miss the delicious breakfast, the special dinner on the cruise, and the beautiful night scenery. 
That’s because you can enjoy Hong Kong cuisine, such as dim sum and har gow, without having to go far.

caption:
If there is only one place you need to add to your next Hunan province itinerary, this should be The Phoenix Ancient Town! 🐦‍🔥

Fenghuang is exceptionally well-preserved with its wooden houses built on stilts along the Tuo River, showcasing traditional Ming and Qing architectural styles, definitely one of the highlight of our Hunan trip. 

Fenghuang’s (鳳凰古城,fènghuáng gǔchéng) history dates back over 1,300 years and js known for its rich cultural heritage, including the Miao and Tujia ethnic minorities.

Just a short train ride separates Fenghuang from Furong so we would recommend you to group those two ancient towns together in your plan and spend one night in each place. Fenghuang felt way more crowded, lively and touristic than Furong but the town’s architecture is really mind-blowing, so worth to visit! Getting lost around those narrow streets and visiting local shops was our favorite activity of the day. 

📍Fenghuang, Hunan, China

caption:
每年解鎖一種國家服飾 
日本和服是我目前穿下來最喜歡的！
推薦大家去京都二年坂 清水寺附近一定要租和服👘
街道上每個小角落穿和服拍照都很有感 很漂亮
奈奈屋的和服款式很多樣也維護的很好
重點裡面的店員會說中文！
還有學生方案CP值很高還有免費髮型設計
可以租了和服一路走到清水寺邊走邊拍照
建議早一點來因為沒有限時只要17:30關門前還就可以了！

cleaned_caption: Unlock a national costume every year. Japanese kimono is my favorite thing to wear. I recommend you to go to Kyoto Nienzaka. You must rent kimono near Kiyomizu Temple. Every small corner of the street is very touching to take photos. It is very beautiful. Nanaya’s kimono styles are very different and well maintained. The clerks in the key points speak Chinese. There are also student plans, and the CP value is very high and there are free hairstyles. You can rent kimono all the way to Kiyomizu Temple and take photos while walking. It is recommended to come earlier because there is no time limit. Just 1730 before closing. caption:
📍Kyoto, Japan
Nu al 1,5 week in Japan 🇯🇵 (Tokyo & Kyoto) en dit is zo mijn ding! De enorm vriendelijke & gastvrije mensen, het heerlijke eten, de mooie bezienswaardigheden en de winkeltjes ☺️ Iedereen is rustig & maakt zich niet zo druk voor mijn gevoel. Kan ik wat van leren 😆

Tokyo is een stad waar ik nu al van weet: ‘Ik wil hier terugkomen!’ 🤞🏼 Ik loop nog achter met de stories, sorry, maar deze stad heeft veel te bieden. Ook met slecht weer, want dat hebben wij helaas ook gehad 🌧️

De volgende dagen bezoeken we nog meer van Kyoto… wordt vervolgd 🎬

caption:
Malayan Settlement: A Fresh Take on Halal Dining in Clarke Quay. For those seeking a unique dining experience in Singapore, Malayan Settlement is a great option to consider. 

From the moment you walk in, you're greeted with a warm and inviting ambiance. The café’s interior seamlessly combines modern aesthetics with ample natural light, creating a cozy and relaxing atmosphere. 

A Menu Full of Surprises; Malayan Settlement impresses with its innovative approach to Southeast Asian cuisine. The menu takes inspiration from traditional Malay flavors while infusing them with a contemporary twist, all while being entirely halal-friendly.  

Here’s what we tried:  

🍴Nasi Lemak Risotto ($32) – A creative take on a beloved classic! This dish features al-dente Arborio rice paired with crispy fried chicken wings, quail eggs, sambal, peanuts, and ikan bilis—a delightful fusion of flavors and textures.  

🍄 Mushroom Soup ($18) – A comforting, earthy soup made from a blend of brown mushrooms, oyster mushrooms, and shiitake mushrooms. Perfectly rich and best enjoyed with bread!  

🥗 Chee Cheong Fun Salad ($21) – A refreshing and unique starter featuring silky rice rolls drizzled with sesame soy sauce, crispy fried onions, ice plant, and a hint of chili for a well-balanced bite.  

🍝Prawn Bisque Pasta ($29) – A hearty, flavorful dish featuring perfectly al-dente pasta coated in a rich, umami-packed prawn bisque sauce.  

🍰Ondeh One For Me ($24) – A show-stopping dessert that tastes as good as it looks! This indulgent treat is a must-try for those with a sweet tooth.  

🍹Malayan Mojito ($19) – A refreshing mix of fresh mint, calamansi, gula melaka, and soda—perfect for a tropical twist on a classic mojito.  

🍸Cucumber Lemonade ($18) – A light and revitalizing drink made with cucumber, lemon, and thyme, offering a perfect balance of citrusy freshness.  

If you’re on the lookout for a halal café with a creative menu, great service, and a welcoming atmosphere, Malayan Settlement should be on your list!

📍3 River Valley Rd, Blk B, 01-03, Singapore 179024

caption:
#MAKINIKIA: HEKAYA FUPI YA MARINA BAY SANDS, NGOME YA ANASA YA NCHI NA MJI WA SINGAPORE

Marina Bay Sands ni moja ya maajabu ya kisasa ya jiji la Singapore katika nchi ambayo nayo inaitwa Singapore, ikiwasha moto wa matajiri na watalii waliotayari kufungua pochi zao bila huruma. 

Elewa kwamba Singapore ni jiji na pia ni nchi huru katika Asia ya Kusini-Mashariki, lenye ukubwa wa kilomita za mraba 728 lakini ina wakazi zaidi ya milioni 5!

Na jiji  hilo lina  uchumi imara wenye Pato la Taifa la takriban dola bilioni 500 kwa mwaka. Ni kitovu cha fedha na biashara duniani, kikiwa na miundombinu bora, utofauti wa kitamaduni na nguvu ya kiuchumi. 

Vitega uchumi vyake vikuu ni usafishaji wa mafuta ghafi (oil refinery), bandari ya pili kwa ukubwa duniani inayolisha bandari zingine 600 katika nchi 120 na biashara ya benki na fedha.

Hivyo basi Marina Bay Sands ilipofunguliwa mwaka 2010, ilikuwa kasino ghali zaidi duniani, ikimeza karibu dola bilioni 6.88 za Kimarekani. 

Hii bwana si hoteli tu bali ni mji mdogo wenye minara mitatu iliyounganishwa na Sands SkyPark, jukwaa lenye urefu wa mita 340 lenye muundo wa meli likiwa na bwawa la infinity linalotoa hisia kama uko juu ya dunia ukiogelea.

Ndani yake kuna kila kitu—kutoka maduka ya kifahari (ambayo hayajawahi kuwa na "sale"), kasino yenye meza 500 na mashine 1,600 za slot, mikahawa ya mapishi ya kifalme, ukumbi wa maonyesho, na hata barafu bandia kwa wale wanaotaka kuteleza bila hofu ya baridi.

Ujenzi wake ulisuasua kwa sababu ya mdororo wa uchumi wa 2007–2008, lakini hatimaye ulifunguliwa kwa awamu. Kasino ilianza kuvuta wenye hela tarehe 27 Aprili 2010, na baadaye SkyPark ikafunguliwa Juni. 

Mnamo Februari 2011, tamasha la mwanga Wonder Full lilitangaza kukamilika rasmi kwa ngome hii ya anasa. Hii ni sehemu unayoenda kama unataka kuona utajiri unavyong’aa—au unavyoyeyuka!

#makinikiyayahabari 
#marinabaysands
#singapore

caption:
When it comes to the word “Singapore” the first person that comes to my mind is Sundar Anne. Or “pa” as I call him 💕 I have always wanted to meet him ever since the day we started speaking on Facebook about grief and about the loss of his daughter. It hit me right in the chest. And something told me to reach out. I am glad I did ❤️

I love how vocal pa was about mental health, and the importance of always looking out for your children. I can’t imagine how difficult it was to sit there and go through the memories or recollection of events. He reminded me so much of my dad. And every part of me just wanted to give him a big hug for being the best dad. 

Years later I got my wish. As I was leaving Singapore Pa decided to put his job on hold and travel all the way to just fetch me and send me to the airport. This was the first time we met. And he presented me with a bouquet of flowers. Nearly brought me to tears because it’s been awhile since anyone gave me flowers. And I got to hug him so tight. ❤️ It was an emotional moment for me. 

I’ve always counted my blessings, and Pa has been there for me despite the distance to always keep an eye. He was my shoulder to lean on when dad passed because I knew no one could understand loss better then him. He always calls me his daughter and that makes my heart warm. Thank you for accepting me as yours. Thank you for loving me unconditionally ❤️ You are a blessing to this world and I hope more parents out there are inspired by you. I love you! ✨

#blessings #singapore #seconddad #family
cleaned_caption: When it comes to the word Singapore the first person that comes to my mind is Sundar Anne. Or pa as I call him I have always wanted to meet him ever since the day we started speaking on Facebook about grief and about the loss of his daughter. It hit me right in the chest. And something told me to reach out. I am glad I did I love how vocal pa was about mental health, and the importance of always looking out for your children. I cant imagine how difficult it was to sit there and go through the memories or recollection of events. He reminded me so much of my dad. And every part of me just wanted to give him a big hug for being the best dad. Years later I got my wish. As I was leaving Singapore Pa decided to put his job on hold and travel all the way to just fetch me and send me to the airport. This was the first time we met. And he presented me with a bouquet of flowers. Nearly brought me to tears because its been awhile since anyone gave me flowers. And I got to hug him so tight. It was an emotional moment for me. Ive always counted my blessings, and Pa has been there for me despite the distance to always keep an eye. caption:
久々の海外旅行はシンガポール
北海道の新千歳空港から一本でサクッといける！

家族でも友達同士でもカップルでも楽しめる
そんな素敵な場所だったので
ここを回れば間違いない1日目をご紹介

初日はフォトジェニックスポット巡り

✔カトン地区
カラフルな建物が並んでいるのでどからでも
絵になっちゃいます
シンガポールで撮影しておきたいポイント

✔チャイナタウン
仏牙寺
2007年にできた比較的新しい寺院で
チャイナタウンの新名所である寺院なんです
実は屋上にも見所が🤭
蘭、プルメリア、ヤシが植えられていて
南国の静かで落ち着いた時間を満喫できます
金色の梵字で彩られた円筒状の仏具である
「摩尼車」が置かれていてその大きさは世界最大
摩尼車の内部には経文が収められており
時計回りに回すと読経をしたのと
同じ効果があるとされてるから
何回も回ってしまいました

✔アラブストリート
綺麗なサルタンモスク🕌
面白いアイスクリーム屋さんもある(他リールに)

✔ PS.Cafe
1999年創業の超人気カフェ
PS.Cafeはシンガポール内に現段階10店舗も
入ってわかる物凄く森林からパワーが貰える空間で
ゆっくりお食事を楽しめます

✔フラワードーム
Flower Dome
シンガポールのガーデンズ・バイ・ザ・ベイ内にある、世界最大級のガラス温室
3332枚のガラスパネルで覆われていて圧巻
ガラスのグリーンハウスとして
世界一大きいと2015年にギネス登録されてます

✔ ガーデンズ・バイ・ザ・ベイ
Gardens by the Bay
101ヘクタールの敷地
世界各国の植物を展示している人気の植物園
最大50メートルの高さを誇るスーパーツリーには
頂上部分に展望台があります、見晴らし最高！
(私は明るい時間に行きましたが夜も凄い)

✔レッドハウス
シンガポール飯といえば、チリクラブ
エビチリのカニバージョンみたいな味で
チャーハンやパンにかけて食べると沼ります

✔リバークルーズ
夕暮れから夜にかけて更に素敵になる景色に感動

✔クラークキー
食事や買い物、アクティビティまで
充実したスポットでリバークルーズ後は回りたい
歩きながら最後は

✔ナイトショー（スペクトラ）
毎晩15分間開催される無料の噴水ショー
これは絶対に見ておきたい、1日の〆に
1日目はこんな感じで回りましたが
撮りどころがありすぎて
別投稿でもフォーカスして配信します

caption:
Мы в Universal studio in Singapore 🇸🇬 
Я так счастлива, что мы оказались здесь: столько эмоций, счастья и радости мы с Алисой здесь получили 🤗

Парк состоит из 7 тематических земель (Голливуд, Нью-Йорк, Научно-фантастический город, Древний Египет, Затерянный мир, Дальний путь и Мадагаскар), расположенных вокруг лагуны, и включает в себя 24 аттракциона и шоу. 

Нам очень понравилось 😍Больше всего запомнился в замке «Шрека» 4д кинотеатр , давно в меня так никто не плевал 🤣 На самом деле спецэффекты были мощные, начиналось всё со скачков на кресле , а потом и ветер подул, и дождик пошел, вообще улет 😃Всем советую 🫶

Только не понравилось стоять в очередях на аттракционы, и я, кстати, вдвоем с Алисой успела на взрослых аттракционах тоже по одному разу покататься. Если захочется, можно прийти пораньше и успеть все 🫶Или взять за 7.700₽ экспресс-билет и проходить без очереди на аттракционы, только нюанс! Экспресс билет действует не на все горки 😩, в основном, на взрослые.
По поводу еды в парке: как я говорила в сторис, есть в Сингапуре совсем нечего, все жареное, острое и невкусное..Ребенку кроме фри, бургеров, наггетсов и риса, есть нечего.
А так настроение огонь 🔥 

Часы работы парка с 10 утра до 8 вечера, а после парка мы успели в комнату к Harry Potter
NSIONS OF MAGIC заглянуть , которая работала до 10 вечера и находится рядом с парком.
cleaned_caption: We are in Universal Studio in Singapore I'm so happy that we have been here so much emotions, happiness and joy, Alice and I got the park, the park consists of 7 thematic lands of Hollywood, New York, the Scientific and Fantastic City, Ancient Egypt, the lost world, the distant path and the Madagascar located around the lagoon, and includes 24attraction and show.We really liked the most remembered in the castle of Schrek 4D cinema, for a long time no one spit in me in fact the special effects were powerful, it all started with the jumps on the chair, and then the wind blew, and the rain went, in general, I advise everyone to stand in lines on the attractions, and by the way, I also managed to go to adult attractions on adult attractionsTo ride one time.If you want, you can come early and have time or take everything for 7.700 an express ticket and pass without a line for the attractions, only a nuance!The express ticket does not act on all slides, mainly on adults.As for the food in the park, as I said in Storis, there is nothing in Singapore at all, everything is fried, acute and tasteless .. except for freegers, burgers, nuggets and rice, there is nothing.And so the mood is the fire of the park from 10 a.m. to 8 pm, and after the park we managed to look into the room to Harry Potter Nsions of Magic, which worked until 10 pm and is located next to the park.

caption:
Мы в Сингапуре 🛫
Самый лучший аэропорт мира 😍 В этом аэропорту можно гулять весь день ))Называется он Чанги в Сингапуре.
В Чанги в буквальном смысле встроили тропический лес с фантастическим водопадом в новое здание Jewel Changi Airport. Искусственный водопад стал самым высоким в мире 😍

В аэропорту мы провели часа 4, там много развлечений для детей, фонтан вы можете увидеть абсолютно бесплатно.
На 3 этаже есть Canopy park attraction , если заплатить 1200₽ за двоих, вы сможете с ребенком насладиться зеленым парком , детскими площадками и горками , верёвочный парк можно посетить за отдельную плату. Это одно сплошное удовольствие:  проводить время здесь, пока ждёшь следующий рейс.

Для граждан России в Сингапуре действует безвизовый транзитный режим длительностью до 96 часов ( 4 дня) именно поэтому мы здесь остались на 3 дня) Если планируете задержаться в Сингапуре дольше 96 часов, понадобится туристическая виза. Она может быть однократной или многократной, но, в любом случае, максимальный срок безвыездного пребывания - не более 30 дней.

При посещения Сингапура для граждан России обязательно нужно иметь билет на самолет через третью страну. Мы показали на паспортном контроле в электронном виде авиабилеты в третью страну и заполненную иммиграционную карту.

Честно, нам вполне хватило времени 3-4 дня , чтобы увидеть этот прекрасный город Сингапур 🇸🇬#singapore #airportchangi #сингапур
cleaned_caption: In Singapore, we are the best airport in the world at this airport you can walk all day called Changi in Singapore.In Changs, they literally built a tropical forest with a fantastic waterfall in the new Jewel Changi Airport building.The artificial waterfall became the highest in the world at the airport we spent 4 hours, there are a lot of entertainment for children, you can see the fountain absolutely free.On the 3rd floor there is Canopy Park Attraction, if you pay 1200 for two, you can enjoy a green park, playgrounds and slides with your child, a rope park can be visited for a fee.This is one continuous pleasure to spend time here while you are waiting for the next flight.For Russian citizens in Singapore, there is a visa -free transit regime up to 96 hours 4 days, which is why we stayed here for 3 days if you plan to linger in Singapore for longer than 96 hours, you will need a tourist visa.It can be single or multiple, but, in any case, the maximum period of a non -residence of no more than 30 days.When visiting Singapore for Russian citizens, you must definitely have a plane ticket through a third country.We showed air tickets to the third country and a full immigration map at the passport control in electronic form.Honestly, we have enough time for 34 days to see this beautiful city Singapore AirportChangi Singapore

Located at 4 Seton Close, just a stone's throw from Orchard and the Singapore Botanic Gardens, this two-storey 1920s house sits on 30,139 square feet of prime land and is surrounded by lush greenery. 

Bidding for residential rental is currently open and will close on February 28.

caption:
⬇️ These 7 incredible places in Singapore will leave you speechless 😮 @visit_singapore

1. The Super Tree Grove in the Gardens by the Bay is FREE to visit. They have a light & music show every evening after sunset. Make sure to be here earlier to reserve the best spot & watch the sunset.

2. The Tree Tunnel at Fort Canning Park is a beautiful photo spot 🌿 but make sure to come early to take a photo or you will have to wait a bit in line.

3. The Jewel is actually located in a mall at the Arrival Terminal at Changi Airport. You can come here before or after your flight - but make sure to plan enough time.

4. The OCBC Skyway connects the Super Trees from above & lets you see them from a unique perspective. The entrance fee is around 7€y

5. My favorite bar in Singapore with a golden 20‘s interior ✨ they are open for lunch or evening cocktails (they have a strict elegant dress code in the evening)

6. The Cloud Forest is located in the Gardens by the Bay. Plan your visit around the misting time for the best atmosphere, happening every 2 hrs starting from 10 am.

7. Is this the coolest gate in the world? You find it at Terminal 2 at Changi Airport after the Check In Gates.

caption:
My thoughts on the new Prada Café in Singapore 🇮🇹✨

The design is more minimal than I expected—unlike the Milan location, which leans into old-school Italian charm (probably because it’s run in collaboration with Marchesi 1824). This one, however, is fully by Prada itself.

The food is perfect for a luxe coffee break or a chic breakfast, with pastries, sandwiches, and great tea-time bites. They do have more substantial mains like burrata and cocktails too.

Do I think the Milan experience is better? Yes. But if you can’t hop on a flight to Europe for coffee, this is definitely the next best thing. Prices are on the higher side (menu and prices shown in the video), but it’s a fun indulgence at least once. 

The cafe opened to the public this weekend. 

Would you try it? 👀

caption:
Singapore’s coffee culture was one of our favorite parts of our trip. While Boston has it’s own love for coffee, in Singapore the coffee culture is next level! Known as “Kopi”, it is the national drink of Singapore and there are endless variations that you can choose from! We went on a culinary adventure to discover the different forms, from lesser-seen variations, to heritage brews, to modern creations. At each of these spots we were able to try a new version and pair it with delicious bites like coffee chiffon cake, and kaya toast. #VisitSingapore @visit_singapore #MadeinSingapore #Singapore #Twotastebuddiez

📍Nanyang Old Coffee (@nanyangoldcoffee): Classic Kopi O brewed in the traditional manner of a kopi sock paired with Singaporean Snacks
📍Tong Ah Eating House: Kaya french toast paired with a suprisingly rich and delicious butter kopi
📍Chin Mee Chin Confectionery (@chinmeechin.sg): Double the kopi flavor with a light and flavorful coffee chiffon cake paired with kopi kosong 
📍MO Bar (@mobarsg): enjoy a boozy twist with boozy kopi siew dai while overlooking the Marina Bay Sands
📍Coffee Break (@coffeebreakamoy): Classic kopi brewed hawkers style with modern flavors like almond sesame and cinnamon paired with matcha & black sesame toast

caption:
making sure everyone’s still crazy & rich 🤍 lil Singapore dump! Swipe to last slide to see what my sister packed in my goody bag

THINGS TO DO IN SINGAPORE:
1. Download @grab_sg when you first arrive! It’s pretty much the Uber of Asia and you can order food and get rides. 
2. Take photos near @marinabaysands if you want any iconic photos. 
3. Take a tour of the @gardensbythebay! You can easily spend a couple hours hear and it’s a nice escape from the heat. 
4. Have brunch at @panpacificsingapore! The view is insane on the 70th floor, it overlooks MBS and the Ferris wheel! 
5. Eat lots of Chicken Rice! I’m sad I didn’t eat this for every meal. We went to @boontongkee_sg and it was 10/10!
6. Get a facial and laser treatment at @e.thosclinic! Adeline was incredible and the owner, Eve, is the sweetest. Also it’s hands down the most aesthetic medical spa I’ve ever seen. 
7. Shop on Orchard Road where there are multiple giant malls on the same street, some cute stores I found are @ksisters.sg @supergurl & @lovebonito 
8. Go find my besties Sephora ad! @mikirai 
9. Overall, wear lots of sunscreen, get ready to sweat, and start questioning if you fully understand English or not

caption:
Eat your greens takes a whole new ✨sweet✨ meaning in Singapore 🇸🇬

Singapore’s food scene is as creative as it is rooted in tradition! Each dish I tried on my culinary adventure celebrated “green” elements through pandan. 🍃 Here’s what I loved about these treats:

📍 Chendol at @eatalleysg 
A refreshing shaved ice dessert with pandan jelly “noodles,” creamy coconut milk, and rich palm sugar syrup. The combination of cold, creamy, and chewy textures made this so satisfying in the tropical heat! 🍧🌴

📍 Ondeh Ondeh at @bengawan_solo_sg 
Chewy pandan glutinous rice balls filled with molten palm sugar and coated in freshly grated coconut. I loved the burst of syrupy sweetness in the center—it was such a fun, bite-sized surprise! 🥥

📍 Kueh Salat Ice Cream at @xiaoyatou.sg 
A classic kueh transformed into ice cream! The pandan custard flavors were smooth and fragrant, while the chewy butterfly pea flower glutinous rice bits added a delightful textural contrast. I was surprised at how perfectly nostalgic this felt in ice cream form. 🍨

📍 Pandan Kaya Iced Latte at @loushang.prinsep 
Coffee with a local twist! The pandan syrup added just the right amount of sweetness and fragrance to the iced latte. It’s a drink I’d definitely order again. ☕️🧊

📍 Kaya Cake at @sinpopobrand 
Soft and fluffy pandan sponge cake layered with kaya. The light, airy texture paired with the richness of the kaya made this dessert feel indulgent but not too heavy. Perfect for anyone who enjoys a delicate, layered treat! ☁️

📍 Pandan Gula Melaka Ice Cream at @kindkones_sg 
A guilt-free plant-based treat made with creamy coconut milk. I loved the smooth, silky texture and how the pandan and gula melaka flavors shined through—it’s both refreshing and indulgent. 💚

Each dish gave me a new appreciation for how pandan’s delicate yet fragrant flavor can be used in so many creative ways. Let me know which one you’d try first!

caption:
Henna during Ramadan and Eid holds a special place in my heart. It’s not just about creating beautiful designs—it’s about tradition, connection, and celebrating the joy of the season together. Every year, we have the privilege of meeting our regular customers, many of whom have become like family. We catch up on life, share stories, and continue this cherished yearly ritual that brings us all closer.

This year is even more exciting as we welcome more talented artists to our team, each bringing their unique touch to the craft. With fresh creativity and passion, we’re ready to make this season even more special. I truly can’t wait to share the love of henna art with all of you, creating designs that symbolize beauty, blessings, and the spirit of Eid. Let’s celebrate together and make this year’s henna experience unforgettable!

✨ ArtScience Museum at Marina Bay Sands Singapore - Future World: Where Art Meets Science @artsciencemuseumsg

✨ ArtScience Museum at Marina Bay Sands Singapore - The World of Studio Ghibli (ended on February 2nd, 2025) 

✨ S.E.A. Focus @ SAW 2025 at Tanjong Pagar Distripark (ended on January 26th, 2025) @seafocus

I was impressed by the diversity of the art on display and the vibrant atmosphere during Singapore Art Week 2025. caption:
[REVIEW]
I’ve been on a serious dimsum high recently 🥟 Whether it’s xiao long baos, har gows, or siew mai, these treats never disappoint - perfect for one or for sharing! 

If you’re looking to satisfy your dimsum cravings, try @sumdimsumsg! I recently brought my family to their main branch at Jalan Besar and got to try out some of their tasty selections 🤤

They have a promotional seafood menu featuring dishes like Steamed Half Boston Lobster 🦞 and Steamed Oysters 🦪, both prepared with garlic and spring onions! I particularly enjoyed the lobster - the meat was real plump and flavourful ☺️

We ordered a variety of dishes, including their signatures like the Crispy Pandan Pork Bun and Prawn Tiffany Blue XL Har Gows, along with classic dim sum items such as Xiao Long Bao, Siew Mai, and Prawn Rice Rolls 🤤 I highly recommend both signature dishes (they’re signature for a reason 👀) especially the Pandan Pork Bun!

For mains, we tried their Moonlight Hor Fun and XO Stir-Fried Carrot Cake! 🤩 You can also order from their selection of rice and soup dishes to enjoy your dimsum feast with that zi char touch 🤭

Overall, this was an awesome treat with my family! You guys should definitely try their dimsum, as well as their promotional seafood dishes 😋 Besides this Jalan Besar outlet, they also have outlets at Bedok and Punggol 🥳 Bring your dimsum buddies along!

Thank you @sumdimsumsg for the invitation! 😊

📍Sum Dim Sum
161 Jalan Besar
Singapore 208876

caption:
[🦆 New Outlet & Concept + 🚨 Opening Promotion]  Introducing Dian Xiao Er Prestige 店小二臻选, now exclusively at Great World!  

As the name suggests, Dian Xiao Er Prestige offers an elevated dining experience with a stunning 170-seater space, featuring elegant wooden furnishings, two VIP rooms (seating 14), and seven semi-private rooms (seating 10) for a more intimate setting.  

While the Signature Herbal Roast Ducks remain a must-try, this new outlet boasts exclusive dishes unavailable at any other Dian Xiao Er.  

Outlet-Exclusive Dishes:  
🍤Tropical Seafood Crunchies (6 pcs - $10.90) – A delightful mix of seafood, deep-fried to perfection and coated in a house-blend sauce.  
🍲Double-boiled Sea Coconut Kampong Chicken with Conpoy ($12.90) – A nourishing soup infused with the natural sweetness of sea coconut.  
🦐Stir-fried Prawns with Wild Mountain Garlic (from $23.90) – Large prawns wok-tossed with fragrant garlic varietals.  
🥚Stir-fried Egg White with Seafood($23.90) – A silky, delicate dish featuring prawns, squid, and fish.  
🍄Jade Essence of Prawn and White Fungus (from $23.90) – A harmonious blend of seafood sweetness and earthy nuttiness.  
🥬Stir-fried Kai Lan with Yellow Rice Wine (from $17.60) – Crisp greens enhanced with aromatic rice wine.  
🐟House Special Fragrant Celery Sauce Steamed Fish – Choose from Sultan King Fish (Whole - $139) or Soon Hock Fish (Whole - $93). Also available: Fish Tail ($25.90) and Fish Slices ($17.60).  
🍜Crab Roe Bee Hoon ($19.90) – A fragrant and flavorful carb dish.  
🍲Golden Prawn Broth with Crispy Rice ($38.90) – A rich and comforting bowl of goodness.  

🚨Opening Promotion (18 Feb - 16 Mar 2025) Order the Crab Roe Bee Hoon and receive a sure-win scratch card! 🎟️ Win either a FREE Crab Roe Bee Hoon or 50% off on your next visit (min. spend $40).  

📍1 Kim Seng Promenade, Great World 01-140, Singapore 237994

caption:
And just like that… another chapter in our lives, called “Singapore,” is coming to an end.

Exactly six years ago, we packed our bags in Japan and set off on an exciting journey to a city I had dreamed about for a long time. We arrived with just two acquaintances and two new jobs.

Fast forward six years, and I can’t even begin to describe how grateful I am for everything Singapore has given us—dozens of amazing friends, hundreds of unforgettable trips, incredible career opportunities, one beautiful dog, and so many once-in-a-lifetime experiences.

But at some point, I started to feel a little stuck. It turns out I had just gotten too comfortable in our little paradise. And, as they say, magic doesn’t happen in your comfort zone.

So here we are, ready to leave the place we’ve called home for the past six years and step into the next adventure. But that’s a story for another time ;)
P.S. Any guesses on where we might be headed next?
*
И вот… ещё одна глава нашей жизни под названием “Сингапур”подходит к концу.

Ровно 6 лет назад мы мы приехали в совершенно незнакомый город, чтобы обустроить тут дом. В кармане было 2 знакомых, 2 предложения по работе и одна квартира, которую мы нашли за три дня.

Спустя шесть лет я даже не могу описать, насколько я благодарна за всё, что дал нам Сингапур: десятки замечательных друзей, сотни незабываемых путешествий, невероятные карьерные возможности, замечательную собаку и множество незабываемых моментов.

Но в какой-то момент мне стало очень тесно в нашем раю. Потому что чудеса не случаются в вашей зоне комфорта. И вот, мы сидим на чемоданах. Но об этом я напишу в следующий раз ;)
P.S. Кто догадается куда?

caption:
Taking care of ourselves can be challenging. It was definitely tough for me, especially post-pandemic.

That’s why we launched DELTA, a first-in-kind study in which I am the test subject (IRB-approved).

DELTA is an interventional trial, and not a health tracking or data collection exercise. The DELTA regimen is comprised of #digital, #fasting, #sleep, #microbiome, carefully-selected supplements, contrast therapy, #fitness, and clean eating, among others. Findings will be reported following peer review.

My n-of-1 DELTA regimen isn’t meant for everyone, but there are lessons that can apply beyond just me.

Here’s one that was unexpected, even if its underpinnings are well known: I never thought that my own children would start prioritising their sleep, based on their dad’s habits. 

Young adults today are among the worst-slept in history. I’m glad that this n-of-1 study has benefited at least 2 others.

Cheers to all those trying to future-proof their health, and for those thinking about it, what makes our #Singapore community so cool is that help is around the corner.

I’m frequently asked why I’m doing this. Aside from taking charge of my own health, it’s quite simple: If any ounce of my learnings help loved ones, friends, and colleagues and maybe even their families stay healthy…WORTH IT.

A huge Shout-Out to our crews from WisDM, N.1, and BME that are driving DELTA.

#health #fitness #optimization #fitfam #strength #HIIT

From being a hardcore HipHop Tamizha fan for years to standing on stage with Aadhi anna himself infront of thousands and thousands of people, this was just beyond my dreams The moment Aadhi anna called me up, my heart was beating fast. Standing under those lights, mic in hand, and hearing the crowd cheer, it was incredible. I have always admired Aadhi anna and Jeeva anna, not just for their music, but for the way they inspire millions, including me. To be up there, even for a few minutes, was an experience of a lifetime. This wasn't just a concert for me. this was proof that dreams do come true, that passion and love for music can take you places you never imagined. I am forever grateful for this moment, for everyone who cheered for me that night, and most importantly, Aadhi anna and Jeeva anna, who mean the world to me. The amount of love I have for both Aadhi anna and Jeeva anna is out of this world. To this day, the two most important people I love after my parents are Aadhi and Jeeva. I do not consider you two as celebrities, singers, or actors, I consider you two as my own big brothers who are always there for me. Thank you so much for calling me, recognizing me, and supporting me, anna. I love you two soooo much! I can't wait to meet you all in Chennai. 🥹❤️

caption:
SAVE THIS‼️ We found a secret Chongqing-style hotpot restaurant in China! 🔥

Located near the viral rooftop carpark above People’s Park Complex in Chinatown, there’s a new hidden hotpot restaurant that many still don’t know about. It’s called Shan Yu Zong, and they are an authentic Chongqing-style hotpot concept that’s getting really popular on 小红书. 📕

For a place this hidden, the decor really impressed us with a rustic charm to it that looks like it belongs in an old street in China. There aren’t a lot of soup bases to choose from with only three options. Of course, their Spicy Red Oil Hotpot is a must; seeing the spicy tallow melt in front of us is an eye-opening experience! 🌶️

You can choose how spicy you want your broth to be, but they only use water for refills, so it gets diluted over time. If you want the soup to be stronger, they do charge an additional $3 for the flavour base. The service here is really quick; our ingredients were served within 5 minutes after placing an order. Portion sizes aren’t too big, which is great if you want to have a variety. There’s a couple of interesting ingredients too that aren’t common elsewhere, like their Fresh Beef Tripe and the Lucky Sausage Skewer. 🐄

Prices here is reasonable too, considering how the 7 of us paid only $40 each to be stuffed. It’s best to make a reservation via calling in before coming here, as we heard they can get crowded during peak timings.

Shan Yu Zong 山渝宗火锅
📍 People’s Park Complex, #06-01/02, 1 Park Road, Singapore
🕙 Open daily, 11.30am to 12mn

cleaned_caption: SAVE THIS We found a secret Chongqingstyle hotpot restaurant in China! Located near the viral rooftop carpark above Peoples Park Complex in Chinatown, theres a new hidden hotpot restaurant that many still dont know about. Its called Shan Yu Zong, and they are an authentic Chongqingstyle hotpot concept thats getting really popular on 小红书. For a place this hidden, the decor really impressed us with a rustic charm to it that looks like it belongs in an old street in China. There arent a lot of soup bases to choose from with only three options. Of course, their Spicy Red Oil Hotpot is a must; seeing the spicy tallow melt in front of us is an eyeopening experience! You can choose how spicy you want your broth to be, but they only use water for refills, so it gets diluted over time. If you want the soup to be stronger, they do charge an additional 3 for the flavour base. The service here is really quick; our ingredients were served within 5 minutes after placing an order. Portion sizes arent too big, which is great if you want to have a variety. Theres a couple of interesting ingredients too that arent common elsewhere, like their Fresh Beef Tripe and the Lucky Sausage Skewer. Prices here is reasonable too, considering how the 7 of us paid only 40 each to be stuffed. Its best to make a reservation via calling in before coming here, as we heard they can get crowded during peak timings. Shan Yu Zong 山渝宗火锅 Peoples Park Complex, 060102, 1 Park Road, Singapore Open daily, 11.30am to 12mn 山渝宗 hotpot sgfoodies singapore sgeats sgfoodblogger hiddengems sgrestaurant sghotpot onericeplease chinatown

caption:
Meillä kävi ihan mieletön tuuri! 

Matkustimme Singaporeen, missä koko matkan pääkohteena tyttärellä oli Singaporen monta kertaa maailman parhaaksi valittu lentokenttä. Kenttä on siis täynnä toinen toistaan upeampia kohteita jo valmiiksi, mutta arvatkaapa mitä! Meidän vierailun aikaan kentällä oli lisäksi käynnissä Hello Kittyn viime vuoden 50-vuotisjuhlavuoden juhlahulinoita!

Kentällä oli upeita installaatioita, pop-up-myymälä ja karnevaalialue. Ja kun on Singaporen kentästä kyse, oli kaikki aivan valtavan suurta ja näyttävää.

Juhlahulinat päättyivät ystävänpäivänä, joten enää tätä ei ole harmillisesti mahdollista nähdä, mutta Singaporen tietäen, kentälle varmasti ilmestyy seuraavana jotain yhtä kiinnostavaa! Ja onhan se jo valmiiksikin aivan mieletön kenttä ilman pop-upejakin.

Tykkäätkö sinä Hello Kittystä, Cinnamorollista, MyMelodysta, Kuromista tai Pompompurinista?

#singapore #changiairport #hellokitty #matkailu
cleaned_caption: We had an insane luck!We traveled to Singapore, where the whole trip the main destination of the daughter was Singapore's many times the world's best airport.So the field is filled with more magnificent destinations already, but guess what!During our visit, Hello Kitty's 50th anniversary celebration was also on the field!There were stunning installations on the field, a pop -up shop and a carnival area.And when it comes to the Singapore field, everything was enormous and spectacular.The party ends ended on Valentine's Day, so it is no longer possible to see this anymore, but with the knowing of Singapore, something equally interesting will probably appear on the field!And it is already ready to be an absolutely insane field without popups.Do you like Hello Kitty, Cinnamoroll, Mymelody, Curm or Pompompurin?Singapore Changiairport Hellitity Tourism

caption:
Suatu kenyamanan tersendiri bisa terbang dengan Singapore Airlines di SQ 388 dari Singapore ke Barcelona tanggal 31 Januari 2025, padahal saya onboard di Kelas Ekonomi loh 😀

Fasiltas penerbangannya terasa lengkap dan beroperasi secara maksimal, inflight entertainementnya banyak pilihan dgn touch screen yang lancar, makanannya pun enak2 dan porsinya bikin kenyang (bisa rusak program diet kalau naik SQ 😀), kabinnya bersih dan wangi, economy legroomnya jg ok, lavatorynya jg lengkap. Wifi pun lancar selama penerbangan dan bisa free untuk anggota Krisflyer. Udah begitu, crewnya ramah2, karena crewnya ramah2, penumpang avgeek seperti saya jadi berani untuk ajak bicara dan selfie. Penerbangan sekitar 13an jam dari Singapore ke Barcelona menjadi tidak terasa.

Semoga saya berkesempatan terbang lagi dengan Singapore Airlines.

#singaporeairlines #airbus #a350 #sq388 #inflight #flightreview #pesawat #singapore
cleaned_caption: A separate comfort can fly with Singapore Airlines on SQ 388 from Singapore to Barcelona on January 31, 2025, even though I am onboard in the economy class, the flight facility feels complete and operates optimally, the inflight entertainment has many choices with a smooth touch screen, the food is delicious and the portion makes the dietOk, the lavatory is also complete.Wifi was smooth during the flight and could be free for Krisflyer members.Already so, the crew is friendly, because the crew is friendly, Avgeek passengers like me are brave to talk and selfie.Flights around 13 hours from Singapore to Barcelona are not felt.Hopefully I have the opportunity to fly again with Singapore Airlines.Singaporeairlines Airbus A350 SQ388 Inflight Flightreview Singapore
